description: For some time after its birth, it grows by taking nourishment from the seed on its back.
name: Bulbasaur

description: When the bud on its back starts swelling, a sweet aroma wafts to indicate the flower’s coming bloom.
name: Ivysaur

description: After a rainy day, the flower on its back smells stronger. The scent attracts other Pokémon.
name: Venusaur

description: The fire on the tip of its tail is a measure of its life. If the Pokémon is healthy, its tail burns intensely.
name: Charmander

description: In the rocky mountains where Charmeleon live, their fiery tails shine at night like stars.
name: Charmeleon

description: It is said that Charizard’s fire burns hotter if it has experienced harsh battles.
name: Charizard

description: It hides in its shell to protect itself, then strikes back with spouts of water at every opportunity.
name: Squirtle

description: It is said to live 10,000 years. Its furry tail is popular as a symbol of longevity.
name: Wartortle

description: The jets of water it spouts from the rocket cannons on its shell can punch through thick steel.
name: Blastoise

description: It releases a stench from its red antennae to repel enemies. It grows by molting repeatedly.
name: Caterpie

description: A steel-hard shell protects its tender body. The Pokémon quietly endures hardships while awaiting evolution.
name: Metapod

description: It loves the nectar of flowers and can locate flower patches that have even tiny amounts of pollen.
name: Butterfree

description: It eats its weight in leaves every day. It fends off attackers with the needle on its head.
name: Weedle

description: While awaiting evolution, it hides from predators under leaves and in nooks of branches.
name: Kakuna

description: Its best attack involves flying around at high speed, striking with poison needles, then flying off.
name: Beedrill

description: It is docile and prefers to avoid conflict. If disturbed, however, it can ferociously strike back.
name: Pidgey

description: It flies over its wide territory in search of prey, downing it with its highly developed claws.
name: Pidgeotto

description: By flapping its wings with all its might, Pidgeot can make a gust of wind capable of bending tall trees.
name: Pidgeot

description: It’s cautious in the extreme, and its hardy vitality lets it live in any kind of environment.
name: Rattata

description: It whittles down its constantly growing fangs by gnawing on hard things. It can chew apart cinder block walls.
name: Raticate

description: It flaps its small wings busily to fly. Using its beak, it searches in grass for prey.
name: Spearow

description: It has the stamina to fly all day on its broad wings. It fights by using its sharp beak.
name: Fearow

description: It sneaks through grass without making a sound and strikes unsuspecting prey from behind.
name: Ekans

description: The pattern on its belly is for intimidation. It constricts foes while they are frozen in fear.
name: Arbok

description: When several of these Pokémon gather, their electricity can build and cause lightning storms.
name: Pikachu

description: If the electric pouches in its cheeks become fully charged, both ears will stand straight up.
name: Raichu

description: To protect itself from attackers, it curls up into a ball. It lives in arid regions with minimal rainfall.
name: Sandshrew

description: It curls up, then rolls into foes with its back. Its sharp spines inflict severe damage.
name: Sandslash

description: While this Pokémon does not prefer to fight, even one drop of the venom it secretes from its barbs can be fatal.
name: Nidoran♀️

description: When it senses danger, it raises all the barbs on its body. These barbs grow more slowly than Nidorino’s.
name: Nidorina

description: Its entire body is armored with hard scales. It will protect the young in its burrow with its life.
name: Nidoqueen

description: It scans its surroundings by raising its ears out of the grass. Its toxic horn is for protection.
name: Nidoran♂️

description: It has a violent disposition and stabs foes with its horn, which oozes venom upon impact.
name: Nidorino

description: One swing of its mighty tail can snap a telephone pole as if it were a matchstick.
name: Nidoking

description: It can be found in quiet mountain areas on a full moon’s night. Its dancing and its tiny, faintly glowing wings confer upon it a lovely fairylike quality.
name: Clefairy

description: Legend says that on clear, quiet nights, it listens for the voices of its kin living on the moon. I, too, often think of my homeland, so far away.
name: Clefable

description: In its belly burns a fire, which Vulpix spits out in the form of fireballs. When young, this Pokémon has but one white tail. As the Pokémon matures, this single tail splits into six.
name: Vulpix

description: The coat of gleaming golden fur is quite magnificent. This species is said to store sacred power in its nine long tails and to live for a millennium.
name: Ninetales

description: If it inflates to sing a lullaby, it can perform longer and cause sure drowsiness in its audience.
name: Jigglypuff

description: The rich, fluffy fur that covers its body feels so good that anyone who feels it can’t stop touching it.
name: Wigglytuff

description: Makes its home in gloomy caves. Atrophied eyes have left this Pokémon blind, so it scans its surroundings via sound waves that it emits from its mouth as it flies.
name: Zubat

description: It sinks its sharp fangs into other creatures and slurps up their blood. A closer look at the fangs reveals that they are hollow and akin to straws.
name: Golbat

description: It often plants its root feet in the ground during the day and sows seeds as it walks about at night.
name: Oddish

description: The nectar it drools from its mouth smells so atrocious that it can make noses curl from more than a mile away.
name: Gloom

description: Its petals are the largest in the world. As it walks, it scatters extremely allergenic pollen.
name: Vileplume

description: Sometimes seen at the foot of trees in humid forests. The mushrooms on its back—called tochukaso—are not present on infant specimens and instead emerge as Paras matures.
name: Paras

description: Mushroom-lacking specimens of this Pokémon lie unmoving in the forest, lending credence to the hypothesis that the large mushroom is in control of Parasect’s actions.
name: Parasect

description: Its eyes act as radar, enabling it to be active in darkness. The eyes can also shoot powerful beams.
name: Venonat

description: When it attacks, it flaps its large wings violently to scatter its poisonous powder all around.
name: Venomoth

description: Its skin is very thin. If it is exposed to light, its blood heats up, causing it to grow weak.
name: Diglett

description: In battle, it digs through the ground and strikes the unsuspecting foe from an unexpected direction.
name: Dugtrio

description: It loves things that sparkle. When it sees a shiny object, the gold coin on its head shines, too.
name: Meowth

description: It has a vicious temperament. Beware if it raises its tail straight up. This is a signal that it is about to pounce and bite.
name: Persian

description: If its chronic headache peaks, it may exhibit odd powers. It seems unable to recall such an episode.
name: Psyduck

description: It swims gracefully along on the quiet, slow-moving rivers and lakes of which it is so fond.
name: Golduck

description: It is extremely quick to anger. It could be docile one moment, then thrashing away the next instant.
name: Mankey

description: Some researchers theorize that Primeape remains angry even when inside a Poké Ball.
name: Primeape

description: It’s very friendly and faithful to people. It will try to repel enemies by barking and biting.
name: Growlithe

description: Its magnificent bark conveys a sense of majesty. Anyone hearing it can’t help but grovel before it.
name: Arcanine

description: Its skin is so thin, its internal organs are visible. It has trouble walking on its newly grown feet.
name: Poliwag

description: The spiral pattern on its belly subtly undulates. Staring at it gradually causes drowsiness.
name: Poliwhirl

description: With its extremely tough muscles, it could keep swimming in the Pacific Ocean without resting.
name: Poliwrath

description: Spends 18 hours of the day sleeping. Even while asleep, Abra can control its psychic powers—should danger approach, the Pokémon will simply teleport away.
name: Abra

description: There are rumors that a child with mystical powers became a Kadabra; however, this remains unverified. I suspect that the spoon Kadabra holds enhances its brain waves.
name: Kadabra

description: The longer Alakazam lives, the larger and heavier its head becomes. Our tests have shown that the strength of its psychic powers correlates positively to the weight of its head.
name: Alakazam

description: Though as small as a child, it has strength enough to easily throw a well-built adult. Striving to become ever stronger, Machop trains by carrying a Graveler on its shoulders.
name: Machop

description: A sturdy creature boasting a robust physique and boundless stamina. Loves training above all else and voluntarily assists with tasks such as construction and clearing land.
name: Machoke

description: In close combat, its four arms afford it offensive and defensive supremacy. In but a blink, this valiant Pokémon can overwhelm its foes with more than 1,000 blows from its fists.
name: Machamp

description: It prefers hot and humid environments. It is quick at capturing prey with its vines.
name: Bellsprout

description: This Pokémon has the appearance of a plant. It captures unwary prey by dousing them with a toxic powder.
name: Weepinbell

description: In its mouth, it pools a fragrant nectar-like fluid. The fluid is really an acid that dissolves anything.
name: Victreebel

description: They fire beams from the glassy, magenta orbs that resemble eyes atop their heads, and they drift in shallow seas. During low tide, they can sometimes be found on beaches, desiccated.
name: Tentacool

description: It has 80 tentacles, each with a venomous tip. These tentacles are also extendible, lengthening when Tentacruel attempts to catch prey. Use caution.
name: Tentacruel

description: Makes its home in mountainous regions, using its arms to climb along harsh mountain roads. Can be troublesome—carelessly kicking one will cause it to fly into a rage and chase after you.
name: Geodude

description: Dwells in holes dug into sheer walls of stone. It enjoys rolling down slopes as though it were a boulder during a rockfall, so keep an eye upward while traversing mountain roads.
name: Graveler

description: The rocklike shell is shed each year. The cast-off shell then crumbles, reverting to a mass of soil, which can be spread across fields to promote crop growth.
name: Golem

description: These Pokémon live in herds out in the grassland. Newborn foals lack their fiery manes, which will develop about an hour after birth.
name: Ponyta

description: Fiery mane aglow, Rapidash darts like an arrow across the land. This prodigiously swift creature can traverse the vast region of Hisui in a day and a half.
name: Rapidash

description: It is always vacantly lost in thought, but no one knows what it is thinking about. It is good at fishing with its tail.
name: Slowpoke

description: If the tail-biting Shellder is thrown off in a harsh battle, this Pokémon reverts to being an ordinary Slowpoke.
name: Slowbro

description: It moves while constantly hovering. It discharges electromagnetic waves and so on from the units at its sides.
name: Magnemite

description: They’re formed by several Magnemite linked together. They frequently appear when sunspots flare up.
name: Magneton

description: It can’t live without the stalk it holds. That’s why it defends the stalk from attackers with its life.
name: Farfetch'd

description: The brains in its two heads appear to communicate emotions to each other with a telepathic power.
name: Doduo

description: When Doduo evolves into this odd breed, one of its heads splits into two. This Pokémon runs at nearly 40 mph.
name: Dodrio

description: This Pokémon lives on icebergs. It uses the sharp point on its head to break up ice as it swims in the sea.
name: Seel

description: In snow, the pure white coat covering its body obscures it from predators.
name: Dewgong

description: When two of these Pokémon’s bodies are combined together, new poisons are created.
name: Grimer

description: It’s so stinky! Muk’s body contains toxic elements, and any plant will wilt when it passes by.
name: Muk

description: Clamping on to an opponent reveals its vulnerable parts, so it uses this move only as a last resort.
name: Shellder

description: When attacked, it launches its spikes in quick volleys. Its innards have never been seen.
name: Cloyster

description: Its body is made of gas. Despite lacking substance, it can envelop an opponent of any size and cause suffocation.
name: Gastly

description: In total darkness, where nothing is visible, Haunter lurks, silently stalking its next victim.
name: Haunter

description: Hiding in people’s shadows at night, it absorbs their heat. The chill it causes makes the victims shake.
name: Gengar

description: This chain of immense stones resembles a giant serpent. Tremors shake the earth above as it burrows deep beneath the ground, feeding on boulders as it goes.
name: Onix

description: When it twitches its nose, it can tell where someone is sleeping and what that person is dreaming about.
name: Drowzee

description: Always holding a pendulum that it swings at a steady rhythm, it causes drowsiness in anyone nearby.
name: Hypno

description: It lives in burrows dug on sandy beaches. Its pincers fully grow back if they are lost in battle.
name: Krabby

description: The larger pincer has 10,000-horsepower strength. However, it is so heavy, it is difficult to aim.
name: Kingler

description: It’s usually found in power plants. Easily mistaken for a Poké Ball, it has zapped many people.
name: Voltorb

description: It explodes in response to even minor stimuli. It is feared, with the nickname of the Bomb Ball.
name: Electrode

description: Its six eggs converse using telepathy. They can quickly gather if they become separated.
name: Exeggcute

description: It is called the Walking Jungle. If a head grows too big, it falls off and becomes an Exeggcute.
name: Exeggutor

description: When it thinks of its dead mother, it cries. Its crying makes the skull it wears rattle hollowly.
name: Cubone

description: The bones it uses have been in its possession since it was born. It has a ferocious nature.
name: Marowak

description: Its legs can stretch to double their length. First-time foes are startled by Hitmonlee’s extensible reach.
name: Hitmonlee

description: When Hitmonchan twists its arm while throwing a punch, the blow will pulverize even concrete. The Pokémon rests after three minutes of fighting.
name: Hitmonchan

description: Wields its long tongue deftly, as though it were an arm. The Pokémon’s viscous saliva, once it has been collected and boiled down, yields a strong and highly useful adhesive.
name: Lickitung

description: Lighter-than-air gases in its body keep it aloft. The gases not only smell; they are also explosive.
name: Koffing

description: It grows by feeding on gases released by garbage. Though very rare, triplets have been found.
name: Weezing

description: Ludicrously strong—when it butts heads with a mountain, it is the mountain that shatters. But its short legs struggle with turns, and it is incapable of stopping unless it collides with something.
name: Rhyhorn

description: Rapidly rotates its horn to bore through bedrock. It swaggers around volcanic regions, protected from the lava’s heat by its tough, armorlike hide.
name: Rhydon

description: It walks carefully to prevent its egg from breaking. However, it is extremely fast at running away.
name: Chansey

description: It is cloaked entirely in blue vines, preventing any glimpse of its true identity. The vines impart a refreshing sensation when chewed—they’re useful as a spice.
name: Tangela

description: It raises its offspring in its belly pouch. It lets its baby out to play only when it feels safe to do so.
name: Kangaskhan

description: It makes its nest in the shade of corals. If it senses danger, it spits black ink and flees.
name: Horsea

description: Its spines provide protection. Its fins and bones are prized as traditional medicine ingredients.
name: Seadra

description: It swims at a steady five knots. If it senses danger, it will strike back with its sharp horn.
name: Goldeen

description: To protect its family, it will fight with its drill-sharp horn. It lives in hollowed rocks in streams.
name: Seaking

description: If Staryu’s body is damaged, it will regenerate as long as the red core remains. The core flashes at midnight.
name: Staryu

description: At the center of its body is a red core that sends mysterious radio signals into the night sky.
name: Starmie

description: The behavior of this clown-like Pokémon reminds one of pantomime. It creates invisible walls using a force emitted from its fingertips.
name: Mr. Mime

description: The sharp scythes on its forearms become increasingly sharp by cutting through hard objects.
name: Scyther

description: Its cries sound like human speech. However, it is impossible to tell what it is trying to say.
name: Jynx

description: Feeds on electrical energy. During sudden showers beneath looming thunderclouds, one can observe Electabuzz scaling tall trees, where the Pokémon will then wait for lightning to strike.
name: Electabuzz

description: Legend has it that this Pokémon was born from the crater of a volcano. When wounded, it bathes in lava to heal its body, much as one would soak in a hot spring.
name: Magmar

description: It grips prey with its pincers until the prey is torn apart. What it can’t tear, it tosses far away.
name: Pinsir

description: They fight each other by locking horns. The herd’s protector takes pride in its battle-scarred horns.
name: Tauros

description: In the distant past, it was somewhat stronger than the horribly weak descendants that exist today.
name: Magikarp

description: It appears whenever there is world conflict, burning down any place it travels through.
name: Gyarados

description: It loves crossing the sea with people and Pokémon on its back. It understands human speech.
name: Lapras

description: It can freely recombine its own cellular structure to transform into other life-forms.
name: Ditto

description: Its genetic code is irregular. It may mutate if it is exposed to radiation from element stones.
name: Eevee

description: Its cell composition is similar to water molecules. As a result, it can’t be seen when it melts away into water.
name: Vaporeon

description: If agitated, it uses electricity to straighten out its fur and launch it in small bunches.
name: Jolteon

description: It fluffs out its fur collar to cool down its body temperature, which can reach 1,650 degrees Fahrenheit.
name: Flareon

description: It has no discernible heartbeat and does not seem to draw breath, and yet it appears to function without issue. I cannot even begin to explain this utterly bizarre anomaly.
name: Porygon

description: It’s a Pokémon that was resurrected from a fossil using modern science. It swam in ancient seas.
name: Omanyte

description: It is thought that this Pokémon became extinct because its spiral shell grew too large.
name: Omastar

description: It is thought to have inhabited beaches 300 million years ago. It is protected by a sturdy shell.
name: Kabuto

description: It is thought that this Pokémon came onto land because its prey adapted to life on land.
name: Kabutops

description: It’s a Pokémon that roamed the skies in the dinosaur era. Its teeth are like saw blades.
name: Aerodactyl

description: This glutton appears in villages without warning and devours the entirety of their rice granaries—such occurrences have long been counted among the gravest of disasters.
name: Snorlax

description: This legendary bird Pokémon can create blizzards by freezing moisture in the air.
name: Articuno

description: This legendary Pokémon is said to live in thunderclouds. It freely controls lightning bolts.
name: Zapdos

description: It is one of the legendary bird Pokémon. Its appearance is said to indicate the coming of spring.
name: Moltres

description: It is born large to start with. It repeatedly sheds its skin as it steadily grows longer.
name: Dratini

description: It is called the divine Pokémon. When its entire body brightens slightly, the weather changes.
name: Dragonair

description: It can fly in spite of its big and bulky physique. It circles the globe in just 16 hours.
name: Dragonite

description: Mewtwo was created by recombining Mew’s genes. It’s said to have the most savage heart among Pokémon.
name: Mewtwo

description: Because it can use all kinds of moves, many scientists believe Mew to be the ancestor of Pokémon.
name: Mew

description: It uses the leaf on its head to determine the air’s temperature and humidity. It loves to sunbathe.
name: Chikorita

description: The buds that ring its neck give off a spicy aroma that perks people up.
name: Bayleef

description: Its breath has the fantastic ability to revive dead plants and flowers.
name: Meganium

description: Hails from the Johto region. Though usually curled into a ball due to its timid disposition, it harbors tremendous firepower.
name: Cyndaquil

description: This creature’s fur is most mysterious—it is wholly impervious to the burning touch of flame. Should Quilava turn its back to you, take heed! Such a posture indicates a forthcoming attack.
name: Quilava

description: It attacks using blasts of fire. It creates heat shimmers with intense fire to hide itself.
name: Typhlosion

description: It has a habit of biting everything with its well-developed jaws. Even its Trainer needs to be careful.
name: Totodile

description: Once it bites down, it won’t let go until it loses its fangs. New fangs quickly grow into place.
name: Croconaw

description: It usually moves slowly, but it goes at blinding speed when it attacks and bites prey.
name: Feraligatr

description: It has a very nervous nature. It stands up high on its tail so it can scan wide areas.
name: Sentret

description: The mother puts its offspring to sleep by curling up around them. It corners foes with speed.
name: Furret

description: It switches its standing foot so quickly that the switch can’t be seen. It cries at the same time every day.
name: Hoothoot

description: If it flips its head upside down, it’s a sign that it is engaged in very complex thinking.
name: Noctowl

description: It’s so timid that it can’t move unless it’s with a swarm. It conveys its feelings through scent.
name: Ledyba

description: It uses starlight as energy. When more stars appear at night, the patterns on its back grow larger.
name: Ledian

description: It sets a trap by spinning a web with thin but strong thread. It waits motionlessly for prey to arrive.
name: Spinarak

description: It attaches silk to its prey and sets it free. Later, it tracks the silk to the prey and its friends.
name: Ariados

description: Its hind limbs have become another set of wings. Crobat expertly maneuvers its four wings to dart in exquisite fashion through even the most confined caves without losing any speed.
name: Crobat

description: It discharges positive and negative electricity from the tips of its antennae to shock its foes.
name: Chinchou

description: Lanturn’s light can shine up from great depths. It is nicknamed the Deep-Sea Star.
name: Lanturn

description: Despite this Pokémon’s cute appearance, those who want to live with one should prepare to be on the receiving end of its electric jolts.
name: Pichu

description: In silhouette, they resemble twinkling starlight. When shooting stars rain from the night sky, Cleffa gather in numbers and dance as though they are indeed incarnations of the stars.
name: Cleffa

description: It likes to sing but is not yet good at it. With praise and encouragement, it will get better little by little.
name: Igglybuff

description: This ovate creature is frequently mistaken for a moving egg when encountered out in the fields or in the mountains. Its guileless smile soothes the soul.
name: Togepi

description: No records exist of Togetic being seen in the wilds. Rumors abound that it evolves under the loving care of a trusted human companion, upon whom the Pokémon then bestows great joy.
name: Togetic

description: It picks food from cactus plants, deftly avoiding buds and spines. It seems to skip about to move.
name: Natu

description: This odd Pokémon can see both the past and the future. It eyes the sun’s movement all day.
name: Xatu

description: Its fleece grows continually. In the summer, the fleece is fully shed, but it grows back in a week.
name: Mareep

description: Because of its rubbery, electricity-resistant skin, it can store lots of electricity in its fur.
name: Flaaffy

description: When it gets dark, the light from its bright, shiny tail can be seen from far away on the ocean’s surface.
name: Ampharos

description: When the heavy rainfall season ends, it is drawn out by warm sunlight to dance in the open.
name: Bellossom

description: The oil-filled tail functions as a buoy, so it’s fine even in rivers with strong currents.
name: Marill

description: By keeping still and listening intently, it can tell what is in even wild, fast-moving rivers.
name: Azumarill

description: To avoid being attacked, it does nothing but mimic a tree. It hates water and flees from rain.
name: Sudowoodo

description: A group of Poliwag and Poliwhirl will form with a Politoed as the leader. Politoed’s cries make the Pokémon of the group obey.
name: Politoed

description: Outside of cold regions, Hoppip can be found practically everywhere. This is because the wind carries this species all over the world.
name: Hoppip

description: When the weather grows cold, Skiploom’s flower closes and the Pokémon cannot photosynthesize, so it flies away to warmer regions.
name: Skiploom

description: Beware its cotton spores. If you accidentally breathe them in, you’ll be racked with coughs and itchiness.
name: Jumpluff

description: This treetop dweller possesses a tail as dexterous as a hand. Ancient writings describe this Pokémon as a one-armed oddity.
name: Aipom

description: It is very weak. Its only means of defense is to shake its leaves desperately at its attacker.
name: Sunkern

description: Since it converts sunlight into energy, it is always looking in the direction of the sun.
name: Sunflora

description: Its frail wings are so thin that one can see clear through them. However, during flight these wings exhibit the power to churn air with force enough to launch a house skyward.
name: Yanma

description: When the temperature cools in the evening, they emerge from water to seek food along the shore.
name: Wooper

description: A dim-witted Pokémon. It doesn’t care if it bumps its head into boats or rocks while swimming.
name: Quagsire

description: It uses the fine hair that covers its body to sense air currents and predict its enemy’s actions.
name: Espeon

description: When darkness falls, the rings on the body begin to glow, striking fear in the hearts of anyone nearby.
name: Umbreon

description: If spotted, it will lure an unwary person into chasing it, then lose the pursuer on mountain trails.
name: Murkrow

description: It has incredible intellect and intuition. Whatever the situation, it remains calm and collected.
name: Slowking

description: It loves to bite and yank people’s hair from behind without warning, just to see their shocked reactions.
name: Misdreavus

description: It is hard to believe these strangely shaped Pokémon are truly living creatures. I’ve pointed out that the species’ many forms resemble writing from other lands; no one will take me seriously.
name: Unown

description: It desperately tries to keep its black tail hidden. This behavior is said to be proof that its tail hides a secret.
name: Wobbuffet

description: Girafarig’s tail has a small head. It instinctively bites at any foe that approaches the Pokémon from behind.
name: Girafarig

description: It spits out a fluid that it uses to glue tree bark to its body. The fluid hardens when it touches air.
name: Pineco

description: Its entire body is shielded by a steel-hard shell. What lurks inside this shell is a total mystery.
name: Forretress

description: If spotted, it escapes by burrowing with its tail. It can float just slightly using its wings.
name: Dunsparce

description: Its tail is tipped by a thick, horrible stinger. To bring down prey, it will first obscure their vision by covering their faces with its body, and then it will use the stinger to inject them with venom.
name: Gligar

description: This Pokémon evolved through use of a strange item. Its body is coated with steel powder and notably hard—not even diamond can leave so much as a scratch.
name: Steelix

description: Small Pokémon flee from its scary face. It is, however, considered by many people to be cute.
name: Snubbull

description: It is timid in spite of its looks. If it becomes enraged, however, it will strike with its huge fangs.
name: Granbull

description: Experienced fishers say they try to catch Qwilfish in the brief moment that these Pokémon become defenseless just after launching poisonous spikes.
name: Qwilfish

description: It swings its eye-patterned pincers up to scare its foes. This makes it look like it has three heads.
name: Scizor

description: It stores berries in its shell. The berries mix with its body fluids to become delicious juices.
name: Shuckle

description: With its herculean powers, it can easily throw around an object that is 100 times its own weight.
name: Heracross

description: This is a smart and sneaky Pokémon. A pair may work together to steal eggs by having one lure the parents away.
name: Sneasel

description: Its paws are soaked in oodles of honey. When nervous, Teddiursa will lick its paws and soon have a smile back on its face.
name: Teddiursa

description: It is quite skilled at climbing trees. If it comes across a Primeape while searching for berries in the treetops, trouble will surely ensue.
name: Ursaring

description: Its body is made of magma. If it doesn’t keep moving, its body will cool and harden.
name: Slugma

description: Its body temperature is roughly 18,000 degrees Fahrenheit. Flames burst from gaps in its shell made of hardened magma.
name: Magcargo

description: Swinub excels at sniffing out mushrooms buried beneath grass or snow. Since ancient times, the people of Hisui have often relied upon this skill.
name: Swinub

description: The long fur of this Pokémon covers its eyes, ears, and even limbs, allowing Piloswine to resist harshly frigid conditions. The Pokémon’s white tusks can be used to defeat its enemies.
name: Piloswine

description: Many live in the clean seas of the south. They apparently can’t live in polluted waters.
name: Corsola

description: Spits water from its mouth with incredible accuracy. It captures Burmy by shooting them down off the branches from which they dangle.
name: Remoraid

description: While Octillery still shoots water from its mouth, the drastic anatomical difference between it and Remoraid meant that for a long time, no one believed the former evolved from the latter.
name: Octillery

description: It always carries its food with it, wherever it goes. If attacked, it throws its food at the opponent.
name: Delibird

description: This calm and gentle Pokémon swims gracefully through the sea. After building speed, it can leap out of the water. It is often misidentified as a bird Pokémon due to this behavior.
name: Mantine

description: Skarmory is clad entirely in ironhard armor. It flies at speeds over 180 mph.
name: Skarmory

description: It uses different kinds of cries for communicating with others of its kind and for pursuing its prey.
name: Houndour

description: Upon hearing its eerie howls, other Pokémon get the shivers and head straight back to their nests.
name: Houndoom

description: It lives in caves on the seafloor and creates giant whirlpools every time it moves.
name: Kingdra

description: It is far stronger than it appears. If a Phanpy is swinging its trunk around and your arm gets hit by it, your arm bone will shatter.
name: Phanpy

description: Donphan is normally a calm Pokémon, but once it is enraged, it will curl its body into a ball and charge at you while rolling.
name: Donphan

description: A bizarre item caused this Pokémon to evolve. While it now exhibits many new gestures and expressions, its biology remains inscrutable.
name: Porygon2

description: It’s said that this Pokémon used to be stronger long ago when it had many enemies, and that it was even able to evolve under its own power.
name: Stantler

description: It marks its territory by using its tail like a paintbrush. There are more than 5,000 different marks.
name: Smeargle

description: It is famous for its eagerness to fight and always nurses injuries from challenging larger foes.
name: Tyrogue

description: It fights while spinning like a top. The centrifugal force boosts its destructive power by a factor of 10.
name: Hitmontop

description: It tests everything by touching with its lips, which remember what it likes and dislikes.
name: Smoochum

description: They generate electricity by spinning their arms. During a thunderstorm, if one hears the lively voices of children out in the wilderness, what one is actually hearing are the voices of Elekid.
name: Elekid

description: This Pokémon lives in volcanic areas. With each breath, sparks spurt from its mouth and nose. When Magby is in good health, its flames gain a yellow tint.
name: Magby

description: It is said that kids who drink Miltank’s milk grow up to become hearty, healthy adults.
name: Miltank

description: The eggs it lays are filled with happiness. Eating even one bite will bring a smile to anyone.
name: Blissey

description: It is said to have fallen with lightning. It can fire thunderbolts from the rain clouds on its back.
name: Raikou

description: It is said that when it roars, a volcano erupts somewhere around the globe.
name: Entei

description: It races around the world to purify fouled water. It dashes away with the north wind.
name: Suicune

description: It is born deep underground. It can’t emerge until it has entirely consumed the soil around it.
name: Larvitar

description: Its shell is as hard as bedrock, and it is also very strong. Its thrashing can topple a mountain.
name: Pupitar

description: In just one of its mighty hands, it has the power to make the ground shake and mountains crumble.
name: Tyranitar

description: It sleeps in a deep-sea trench. If it flaps its wings, it is said to cause a 40-day storm.
name: Lugia

description: Its feathers are in seven colors. It is said that anyone seeing it is promised eternal happiness.
name: Ho-Oh

description: It has the power to travel across time, but it is said to appear only in peaceful times.
name: Celebi

description: The soles of its feet are covered by countless tiny hooks, enabling it to walk on walls and ceilings.
name: Treecko

description: It lives in dense jungles. While closing in on its prey, it leaps from branch to branch.
name: Grovyle

description: The leaves that grow on its arms can slice down thick trees. It is without peer in jungle combat.
name: Sceptile

description: A fire burns inside it, so it feels very warm to hug. It launches fireballs of 1,800 degrees Fahrenheit.
name: Torchic

description: Its kicking mastery lets it loose 10 kicks per second. It emits sharp cries to intimidate foes.
name: Combusken

description: Flames spout from its wrists, enveloping its knuckles. Its punches scorch its foes.
name: Blaziken

description: Using the fin on its head, Mudkip senses the flow of water to keep track of what’s going on around it. Mudkip has the strength to heft boulders.
name: Mudkip

description: Its sturdy legs give it sure footing, even in mud. It burrows into dirt to sleep.
name: Marshtomp

description: It can swim while towing a large ship. It bashes down foes with a swing of its thick arms.
name: Swampert

description: A Pokémon with a persistent nature, it chases its chosen prey until the prey becomes exhausted.
name: Poochyena

description: It chases down prey in a pack. It will never disobey the commands of a skilled Trainer.
name: Mightyena

description: It walks in zigzag fashion. It’s good at finding items in the grass and even in the ground.
name: Zigzagoon

description: It charges prey at speeds over 60 mph. However, because it can only run straight, it often fails.
name: Linoone

description: Likes sap and is abundant in the wild. Why it evolves into various different forms is unknown. One cannot tell from a Wurmple’s appearance which form it will take when it evolves.
name: Wurmple

description: Wraps itself in thin strings of silk while it stores energy for evolution. It can’t extend its limbs and its movement is slow, but its eyes keep a sharp lookout—Silcoon is always on guard.
name: Silcoon

description: A colorful and incredibly beautiful but also greedy Pokémon. In an effort to keep its favorite food all to itself, it will chase away Combee as they try to gather nectar.
name: Beautifly

description: The silk coating its body is thin but sufficiently strong. Cascoon’s silk has a luster and texture superior to that of Silcoon’s, and clothes made using Cascoon silk are regarded as top-notch.
name: Cascoon

description: Tends to be drawn to bonfires on dark nights. Difficult to chase away from settlements because of the way it scatters highly toxic scales.
name: Dustox

description: It looks like an aquatic plant and serves as a ferry for Pokémon that can’t swim.
name: Lotad

description: It has a mischievous spirit. If it spots an angler, it will tug on the fishing line to interfere.
name: Lombre

description: If it hears festive music, all its muscles fill with energy. It can’t help breaking out into a dance.
name: Ludicolo

description: When it dangles from a tree branch, it looks just like an acorn. It enjoys scaring other Pokémon that try to peck at it.
name: Seedot

description: The sound of its grass flute makes its listeners uneasy. It lives deep in the forest.
name: Nuzleaf

description: By flapping its leafy fans, it can whip up gusts of 100 feet per second that can level houses.
name: Shiftry

description: It has a gutsy spirit that makes it bravely take on tough foes. It flies in search of warm climates.
name: Taillow

description: It circles the sky in search of prey and dives sharply to catch its target.
name: Swellow

description: It rides upon ocean winds as if it were a glider. In the winter, it hides food around its nest.
name: Wingull

description: It protects its young in its beak. It bobs on waves, resting on them on days when the waters are calm.
name: Pelipper

description: It is highly attuned to the emotions of people and Pokémon. It hides if it senses hostility.
name: Ralts

description: The cheerful spirit of its Trainer gives it energy for its psychokinetic power. It spins and dances when happy.
name: Kirlia

description: It unleashes psychokinetic energy at full power when protecting a Trainer it has bonded closely with.
name: Gardevoir

description: It secretes a thick, sweet-scented syrup from the tip of its head. It lives on weed-choked ponds.
name: Surskit

description: The antennae have distinctive patterns that look like eyes. When it rains, they grow heavy, making flight impossible.
name: Masquerain

description: If it senses danger, it scatters spores from the top of its head to protect itself.
name: Shroomish

description: The seeds on its tail are made of toxic spores. It knocks out foes with quick, virtually invisible punches.
name: Breloom

description: The way Slakoth lolls around makes anyone who watches it feel like doing the same.
name: Slakoth

description: It is always hungry because it won’t stop rampaging. Even while it is eating, it can’t keep still.
name: Vigoroth

description: This Pokémon lives lying on its side. It only rolls over and moves when there is no more grass to eat.
name: Slaking

description: It grows underground, sensing its surroundings using antennae instead of its virtually blind eyes.
name: Nincada

description: Because they move so quickly, they sometimes become unseeable. They congregate around tree sap.
name: Ninjask

description: It is a discarded bug shell that came to life. Peering into the crack on its back is said to steal one’s spirit.
name: Shedinja

description: Usually, its cries are like quiet murmurs. If frightened, it shrieks at the same volume as a jet plane.
name: Whismur

description: The shock waves from its cries can tip over trucks. It stamps its feet to power up.
name: Loudred

description: Its howls can be heard over six miles away. It emits all sorts of noises from the ports on its body.
name: Exploud

description: It toughens up by slamming into thick trees over and over. It gains a sturdy body and dauntless spirit.
name: Makuhita

description: It stomps on the ground to build power. It can send a 10-ton truck flying with a straight-arm punch.
name: Hariyama

description: Its tail is packed full of the nutrients it needs to grow.
name: Azurill

description: Once the people of Hisui discovered that its red nose always points north, they grew to rely on it greatly when traveling afar. The nose seems to work in a similar way to ancient compasses.
name: Nosepass

description: It can’t stop itself from chasing moving things, and it runs in circles, chasing its own tail.
name: Skitty

description: It is highly popular among Trainers for its sublime fur. It does not keep a nest.
name: Delcatty

description: Materials from gems it has eaten float to the surface of its body and can form an infinite number of patterns among individuals.
name: Sableye

description: Attached to its head is a huge set of jaws formed by horns. It can chew through iron beams.
name: Mawile

description: It usually lives deep in mountains. But when it’s hungry, it shows up at the foot of the mountains and eats railroad tracks and cars.
name: Aron

description: For food, it digs up iron ore. It smashes its steely body against others to fight over territory.
name: Lairon

description: While seeking iron for food, it digs tunnels by breaking through bedrock with its steel horns.
name: Aggron

description: It meditates to heighten its inner energy and to float in the air. It eats one berry a day.
name: Meditite

description: It elegantly avoids attacks with dance-like steps, then launches a devastating blow in the same motion.
name: Medicham

description: Using electricity stored in its fur, it stimulates its muscles to heighten its reaction speed.
name: Electrike

description: It discharges electricity from its mane. The Pokémon creates a thundercloud overhead from which to drop lightning bolts.
name: Manectric

description: It cheers on friends with pom-poms made of sparks. It drains power from telephone poles.
name: Plusle

description: It cheers on friends. If its friends are losing, its body lets off more and more sparks.
name: Minun

description: It communicates with others by lighting up its rear at night. It loves Illumise’s sweet aroma.
name: Volbeat

description: With its sweet aroma, it guides Volbeat to draw signs with light in the night sky.
name: Illumise

description: Though beautiful, it has highly poisonous thorns. There is an old tradition in my homeland wherein one would send these thorns to an opponent to challenge them to a duel.
name: Roselia

description: It has a small heart and brain. Its stomach comprises most of its body, with enzymes to dissolve anything.
name: Gulpin

description: It can swallow a tire whole in one gulp. It secretes a horribly toxic fluid from the pores on its body.
name: Swalot

description: They swarm any foe that invades their territory. Their sharp fangs can tear out boat hulls.
name: Carvanha

description: Its fangs rip through sheet iron. It swims at 75 mph and is known as the Bully of the Sea.
name: Sharpedo

description: On sunny days, it lands on beaches to bounce like a ball and play. It spouts water from its nostrils.
name: Wailmer

description: It’s the biggest of all Pokémon. It can dive to a depth of almost 10,000 feet on only one breath.
name: Wailord

description: The flaming magma it stores in the hump on its back is the source of its tremendous power.
name: Numel

description: If angered, the humps on its back erupt in a shower of molten lava. It lives in the craters of volcanoes.
name: Camerupt

description: Coal is the source of Torkoal’s energy. Large amounts of coal can be found in the mountains where they live.
name: Torkoal

description: Using its tail like a spring, it keeps its heart beating by bouncing constantly. If it stops, it dies.
name: Spoink

description: It uses black pearls to amplify its psychic power. It does a strange dance to control foes’ minds.
name: Grumpig

description: No two Spinda have the same pattern of spots. Their tottering steps hinder the aim of foes.
name: Spinda

description: It makes a conical pit in desert sand and lies in wait at the bottom for prey to come tumbling down.
name: Trapinch

description: It violently shudders its wings, generating ultrasonic waves to induce headaches in people.
name: Vibrava

description: It whips up sandstorms with powerful flaps of its wings. It is known as the Desert Spirit.
name: Flygon

description: It lives in arid locations. Its yellow flowers bloom once a year.
name: Cacnea

description: It lives in deserts. It becomes active at night when it hunts for prey exhausted from the desert’s heat.
name: Cacturne

description: It can’t relax if it or its surroundings are not clean. It wipes off dirt with its wings.
name: Swablu

description: On sunny days, it flies freely through the sky and blends into the clouds. It sings in a beautiful soprano.
name: Altaria

description: If it comes across a Seviper, its fur bristles and it assumes its battle pose. Its sharp claws are its best weapon.
name: Zangoose

description: Constant polishing makes the edge of the blade on its tail extremely sharp. It’s Zangoose’s archrival.
name: Seviper

description: It becomes active on nights with a full moon, so it is said to have some link to the lunar phases.
name: Lunatone

description: This new Pokémon species is rumored to be an avatar of the sun. The Pokémon gives off light while spinning.
name: Solrock

description: It probes muddy riverbeds with its two long whiskers. A slimy film protects its body.
name: Barboach

description: Sighting Whiscash leaping from the water is believed to herald an earthquake.
name: Whiscash

description: Its hardy vitality enables it to adapt to any environment. Its pincers will never release prey.
name: Corphish

description: It is a ruffian that uses its pincers to pick up and toss out other Pokémon from its pond.
name: Crawdaunt

description: It moves by spinning on its foot. It is a rare Pokémon that was discovered in ancient ruins.
name: Baltoy

description: An ancient clay figurine was exposed to a mysterious ray of light, and it came to life as a Pokémon.
name: Claydol

description: It lived on the seafloor 100 million years ago and was reanimated scientifically.
name: Lileep

description: It lives in the shallows of warm seas. When the tide goes out, it digs up prey from beaches.
name: Cradily

description: This Pokémon ancestor was reanimated from a fossil. It lived in the sea and hunted with its claws.
name: Anorith

description: It went ashore after evolving. Its entire body is clad in a sturdy armor.
name: Armaldo

description: It eats anything, so it can even live in polluted streams and lakes. No one pays any attention to it.
name: Feebas

description: It is the world’s most beautiful Pokémon. There are many works of art featuring Milotic.
name: Milotic

description: Its appearance changes with the weather. Recently, its molecules were found to be just like water.
name: Castform

description: It can freely change its body’s color. The zigzag pattern on its belly doesn’t change, however.
name: Kecleon

description: It feeds on the dark emotions of sadness and hatred, which make it grow steadily stronger.
name: Shuppet

description: Strong feelings of hatred turned a puppet into a Pokémon. If it opens its mouth, its cursed energy escapes.
name: Banette

description: I’ve heard that the children of Hisui all begin to behave once they’ve been told the story of how this Pokémon roams about before the witching hour to spirit away misbehaving children.
name: Duskull

description: There are rumors that peeking inside its bandage-wrapped body will cause one to get pulled in through the gaps between the bandages, never to return. I’ve been too scared to verify.
name: Dusclops

description: Delicious fruits grew out from around its neck because it always ate the same kind of fruit.
name: Tropius

description: Can emit waves of air powerful enough to knock out prey taller than itself. I hypothesize that it amplifies the faint sound of wind within its body.
name: Chimecho

description: It senses coming disasters and appears before people only to warn them of impending danger.
name: Absol

description: They grow strong by pushing up against one another en masse. They love eating sweet fruit.
name: Wynaut

description: It is said that a home visited by a Snorunt will prosper. It can withstand cold of −150 degrees Fahrenheit.
name: Snorunt

description: It prevents prey from escaping by instantaneously freezing moisture in the air.
name: Glalie

description: During the season when drift ice approaches the shore, Spheal prefers living on the ice—where fewer predators lurk—rather than the land. Its fur retains heat superbly and resists harsh cold.
name: Spheal

description: Its white whiskers are very sensitive. Sealeo will balance Spheal on the tip of its nose, checking its scent and its feel to be sure the Spheal is healthy.
name: Sealeo

description: Its thick tusks are strong enough to shatter drift ice. They have been known to break, but they will grow back by the next year. The Hisui region is well known for these broken tusks.
name: Walrein

description: It makes a single pearl during its lifetime. The pearl is said to amplify psychic power.
name: Clamperl

description: It lives deep in the sea. With a tail shaped like a small fish, it attracts unsuspecting prey.
name: Huntail

description: It lives at the bottom of the sea. In the springtime, its pink body turns more vivid for some reason.
name: Gorebyss

description: This rare Pokémon was discovered during a deep-sea exploration. It has not changed in over 100 million years.
name: Relicanth

description: During the spawning season, countless Luvdisc congregate at coral reefs, turning the waters pink.
name: Luvdisc

description: Its belief that it will be able to fly one day is apparently the influence of information carried in its genes.
name: Bagon

description: Its armored body makes all attacks bounce off. The armor is too tough, however, making it heavy and somewhat sluggish.
name: Shelgon

description: It becomes uncontrollable if it is enraged. It destroys everything with shredding claws and fire.
name: Salamence

description: They converse with one another by using magnetic pulses. In a swarm, they move in perfect unison.
name: Beldum

description: It is formed by two Beldum joining together. Its steel body won’t be scratched if it collides with a jet.
name: Metang

description: Metang combined to form it. With four brains, it has the intelligence of a supercomputer.
name: Metagross

description: Its entire body is made of rock. If any part chips off in battle, Regirock attaches rocks to repair itself.
name: Regirock

description: Its body is made of ice from the ice age. It controls frigid air of −328 degrees Fahrenheit.
name: Regice

description: Tempered by pressure underground over tens of thousands of years, its body cannot be scratched.
name: Registeel

description: Its body is covered with a down that can refract light in such a way that it becomes invisible.
name: Latias

description: It is a highly intelligent Pokémon. By folding back its forelegs in flight, it can overtake jet planes.
name: Latios

description: It is said to have widened the seas by causing downpours. It had been asleep in a marine trench.
name: Kyogre

description: It had been asleep in underground magma ever since it fiercely fought Kyogre long ago.
name: Groudon

description: It lives in the ozone layer far above the clouds and cannot be seen from the ground.
name: Rayquaza

description: It is said to wake up for just seven days every 1,000 years and use its power to grant any wish.
name: Jirachi

description: An alien virus that fell to earth on a meteorite underwent a DNA mutation to become this Pokémon.
name: Deoxys

description: This Pokémon becomes more energetic the more sunlight there is. The part resembling a shell is similar to silt and is slightly damp and warm to the touch.
name: Turtwig

description: Appears where there is clean spring water. The fruit that grows on the shrubs on its shell is sweet, nutritious, and truly delicious.
name: Grotle

description: This remarkable, large-bodied Pokémon would serve beautifully as borrowed scenery for a garden, and its strength is peerless. Torterra roams the wilderness in search of clean water.
name: Torterra

description: Full of vigor and always in high spirits. It was once known by the name “Lantern-Tail” and feared as some kind of apparition.
name: Chimchar

description: The deeper the blue on its face, the more powerful it will grow to become. It leaps about every which way and lands powerful blows against its opponents with the flame on its tail.
name: Monferno

description: A tall, hardy Pokémon with a dazzling appearance. It shrouds itself in flame and battles as if engaged in dance—truly a sight to behold.
name: Infernape

description: Prefers cold climes and appears along coasts. It’s an adorable little thing—as cute as any child—but it’s also prideful, unwilling to accept handouts from people.
name: Piplup

description: It swims gracefully through the frigid sea and sings with a voice like the roaring tide. It has powerful, sturdy wings and dignity to match.
name: Prinplup

description: Since ancient times, it has been revered by the people of Hisui, who call it the Master of the Waves. Its wings are a match for even master-crafted blades.
name: Empoleon

description: Because they are weak individually, they form groups. However, they bicker if the group grows too big.
name: Starly

description: They maintain huge flocks, although fierce scuffles break out between various flocks.
name: Staravia

description: It never stops attacking even if it is injured. It fusses over the shape of its comb.
name: Staraptor

description: Bidoof has an unsophisticated face and is rarely flustered by anything. There have been incidents involving Bidoof sauntering into villages and gnawing on the houses without a single care.
name: Bidoof

description: Bibarel fur repels water and is also a fantastic material for heat retention. These Pokémon create dams on rivers to live in.
name: Bibarel

description: When its antennae hit each other, it sounds like the music of a xylophone.
name: Kricketot

description: There is a village that hosts a contest based on the amazingly variable cries of this Pokémon.
name: Kricketune

description: The extension and contraction of its muscles generates electricity. Its fur glows when it’s in trouble.
name: Shinx

description: By gathering their tails together, they collectively generate powerful electricity from their claws.
name: Luxio

description: Luxray’s ability to see through objects comes in handy when it’s scouting for danger.
name: Luxray

description: When the sun’s light strengthens, the bud atop this Pokémon’s head opens. This is a sign to the people that the harsh winter is over, and the season of budding has begun.
name: Budew

description: Hidden within the bouquet on each hand are thorned whips loaded with virulent poison. Roserade moves gracefully as it corners its prey and mercilessly lashes them with its whips.
name: Roserade

description: An incredibly rare sight. They duel each other by ramming their heads together, and the resulting sound echoes throughout the area like the pealing of a bell.
name: Cranidos

description: Very little is known about its biology. Can knock down massive trees by smashing its beautiful, pearl-like crown against them.
name: Rampardos

description: Much remains unknown about this Pokémon, as few have ever seen it. However, we know that it is calm and dislikes conflict, and it enjoys polishing its face against trees and rocks.
name: Shieldon

description: Its face is sturdy—as strong as diamond—and this hardness offers a very stable defense. Much about this species is still unknown, such as its natural habitat.
name: Bastiodon

description: If its cloak is even slightly damaged, Burmy will immediately repair it with whatever is close at hand. The Pokémon within the cloak is scrawny and vulnerable to the cold.
name: Burmy

description: The cloak—fashioned from plant matter—has merged with the Pokémon and is now part of the body, like fur or skin. I suspect this fusion is an effect of the energy involved in evolution.
name: Wormadam

description: Scatters steel-colored scales as it flaps its wings. Despite being observed feeding primarily on the nectar of flowers, Mothim is not often seen around flower gardens.
name: Mothim

description: The trio is together from birth. It constantly gathers nectar from flowers to please Vespiquen.
name: Combee

description: It raises grubs in the holes in its body. It secretes pheromones to control Combee.
name: Vespiquen

description: A pair may be seen rubbing their cheek pouches together in an effort to share stored electricity.
name: Pachirisu

description: It inflates its flotation sac, keeping its face above water in order to watch for prey movement.
name: Buizel

description: It is a common sight around fishing ports. It is known to rescue people and help fishers carry what they caught.
name: Floatzel

description: Once the fruit growing alongside the main body is large and plump, Cherubi will use the nutrients within to evolve. The fruit then detaches, becoming nourishment for other creatures.
name: Cherubi

description: Motionless, save for the occasional quiver. A rich array of Pokémon can be found gathered around it, drawn by the scent exuded from Cherrim’s folded petals.
name: Cherrim

description: It oozes a purple fluid to deter enemies. Apparently, there are more West Sea Shellos now than there were in the past.
name: Shellos

description: It appears on beaches where the waters are shallow. Once it catches prey, it will slowly melt them with its mucus before slurping them up.
name: Gastrodon

description: To affirm their kinship, members of this species will form a ring by linking their newly doubled tails together. On rare occasions, humans have been accepted into such rings.
name: Ambipom

description: Because of the way it floats aimlessly, an old folktale calls it a “signpost for wandering spirits.”
name: Drifloon

description: They carry people and Pokémon, but the wind can catch them, so there can’t be a fixed destination.
name: Drifblim

description: My hypothesis as to why Buneary rolls up its ears is that its hearing is far too keen. I surmise that the Pokémon protects its hearing by limiting the sound that may enter its ears.
name: Buneary

description: Its fur is warm and yet remarkably light. This Pokémon kicks as though it were a master of karate, driving back its opponents with ease.
name: Lopunny

description: Its cries sound like incantations to torment the foe. It appears where you least expect it.
name: Mismagius

description: A single cry from this nocturnal Pokémon, and more than 100 of its Murkrow cronies will assemble.
name: Honchkrow

description: Bewitches humans with its helical tail and piercing gaze. Its hidden claws are quite sharp as well, making this Pokémon an exceedingly tricky opponent if antagonized.
name: Glameow

description: Though impudent and difficult to tame, Purugly enjoys great popularity due to its fur, the beauty of which surpasses even velveteen.
name: Purugly

description: This Pokémon gave me an excruciating headache when it seemingly cried out without making a sound. Perhaps there are some sounds that the human ear is simply incapable of hearing.
name: Chingling

description: The foul fluid from its rear is so revolting that it can make people feel queasy up to a mile and a quarter away.
name: Stunky

description: It attacks by spraying a repugnant fluid from its tail, but the stench dulls after a few squirts.
name: Skuntank

description: They are found in ancient tombs. The patterns on their backs are said to be imbued with mysterious power.
name: Bronzor

description: It brought rains by opening portals to another world. It was revered as a bringer of plentiful harvests.
name: Bronzong

description: From its eyes, it can expel excess moisture from its body. This liquid is similar in composition to human sweat.
name: Bonsly

description: Known to turn up in bustling marketplaces now and again. It mimics people much as a child would, then watches how they react, eyes sparkling.
name: Mime Jr.

description: It carefully carries a round, white rock that it thinks is an egg. It’s bothered by how curly its hair looks.
name: Happiny

description: A versatile performer skilled in the imitation of human speech. It is said that older, more experienced Chatot can even understand the meaning of the words they mimic.
name: Chatot

description: It was formed by uniting 108 spirits. It has been bound to the Odd Keystone to keep it from doing any mischief.
name: Spiritomb

description: It nests in horizontal holes warmed by geothermal heat. Foes who get too close can expect to be pounced on and bitten.
name: Gible

description: It loves sparkly things. It seeks treasures in caves and hoards the loot in its nest.
name: Gabite

description: The protuberances on its head serve as sensors. It can even detect distant prey.
name: Garchomp

description: Its robust stomach allows it to nonchalantly devour even rotted matter. It pays frequent visits to villages, seeking out food scraps intended for compost.
name: Munchlax

description: It has the peculiar power of being able to see emotions, such as joy and rage, in the form of waves.
name: Riolu

description: A well-trained one can use its aura to identify and take in the feelings of creatures over half a mile away.
name: Lucario

description: It shrouds itself in sand to ward off germs. It travels easily through the sands of the desert.
name: Hippopotas

description: It brandishes its gaping mouth in a display of fearsome strength. It raises vast quantities of sand while attacking.
name: Hippowdon

description: Its claws are not only razor-sharp but poisonous, making Skorupi a highly dangerous Pokémon. It seems to be weakened by cold temperatures, however.
name: Skorupi

description: Has a brutish, ferocious temperament. With immense strength and a sturdy shell off which swords will bounce, it rampages about and wreaks havoc.
name: Drapion

description: It rarely fights fairly, but that is strictly to ensure survival. It is popular as a mascot.
name: Croagunk

description: It has a poison sac at its throat. When it croaks, the stored poison is churned for greater potency.
name: Toxicroak

description: Though this is a plant Pokémon, it has a gluttonous and unruly temperament. Carnivine attacks its prey with its cavernous maw wide open.
name: Carnivine

description: It absorbs sunlight with the pink areas of its skin, which then shine. This appears to be a form of camouflage.
name: Finneon

description: Lumineon swimming in the darkness of the deep sea look like stars shining in the night sky.
name: Lumineon

description: Though ball-like in shape, this Pokémon is a proficient swimmer. I have discovered that if a Mantyke spends much time with schools of Remoraid, it will eventually achieve evolution.
name: Mantyke

description: Seemingly curious about people, they gather around footsteps they find on snowy mountains.
name: Snover

description: They appear when the snow flowers bloom. When the petals fall, they retreat to places unknown again.
name: Abomasnow

description: They travel in groups of four or five, leaving signs for one another on trees and rocks. They bring down their prey with coordinated attacks.
name: Weavile

description: Exposure to a special magnetic field changed Magneton’s molecular structure, turning it into Magnezone.
name: Magnezone

description: Its tongue can extend and contract freely, and it is capable of reaching lengths over 10 times Lickilicky’s height. Beware of the saliva, as it contains corrosive elements.
name: Lickilicky

description: This Pokémon evolved through use of a curious item. Its rocklike hide is composed of a mysterious substance and can withstand a blow from a masterwork sword with nary a scratch.
name: Rhyperior

description: Draped with long vines, it resembles a shrub in appearance. It swings bundles of vines as though they were arms, wrapping them around prey to ensnare them.
name: Tangrowth

description: Its evolution was induced by an unusual item, and its electrical output rises along with its heart rate. From its tails, it can unleash an electric current measuring 20,000 volts.
name: Electivire

description: Use of a strange item caused this Pokémon to evolve. Fireballs launched from the ends of its tubelike arms are hot enough to melt an iron pot in an instant.
name: Magmortar

description: Scant few have ever sighted this Pokémon. After studying what literature remains, I am certain Togekiss will reveal itself when peace reigns in the land.
name: Togekiss

description: Extremely violent. When hunting, it wastes none of its energy, aiming only for prey’s most vulnerable spots. Any who manage to tame this Pokémon must be of incredible bravery.
name: Yanmega

description: The younger they are, the more they smell like fresh grass. With age, their fragrance takes on the odor of fallen leaves.
name: Leafeon

description: It lowers its body heat to freeze its fur. The hairs then become like needles it can fire.
name: Glaceon

description: It glides soundlessly on pitch-black wings and sinks sharp fangs into the throat of its prey. It takes on a look of satisfaction once it has entirely drained its prey of blood.
name: Gliscor

description: This species reached its zenith during the period known as the ice age. I suspect that Hisui’s frigid climate is in harmony with Mamoswine’s constitution, thus awakening hidden potential.
name: Mamoswine

description: A curious item induced this evolution. The Pokémon’s offensive capabilities have greatly increased, but the strangeness of its behavior has magnified in equal measure. This worries me.
name: Porygon-Z

description: Because it can sense what its foe is thinking, its attacks burst out first, fast, and fierce.
name: Gallade

description: It is able to emit powerful magnetism, allowing it control over the iron sand that forms its luscious mustache. Using this iron sand, Probopass forms hard stones with which it smites its prey.
name: Probopass

description: Comes to those whose lives have come to an end and escorts their souls to the afterlife. Known to mistakenly take the souls of those who yet have life left in them, albeit rarely.
name: Dusknoir

description: It freezes prey by blowing its −58 degree Fahrenheit breath. It is said to then secretly display its prey.
name: Froslass

description: Research continues on this Pokémon, which could be the power source of a unique motor.
name: Rotom

description: A Pokémon feared but also respected for stealing away the memories of evildoers. I have found records that suggest Uxie holds dominion over knowledge.
name: Uxie

description: Known as the Being of Emotion. In legend, this Pokémon was feared, as any who showed disrespect would have their emotions thrown into disarray.
name: Mesprit

description: The dreaded Being of Willpower. Legends tell of this Pokémon manipulating the will of its adversaries and turning them into puppets of its own.
name: Azelf

description: This Pokémon is revered as a deity in Hisuian legend. The birth of Dialga was what caused the vast river of time to begin flowing in our world.
name: Dialga

description: This Pokémon is feared as a deity in Hisuian legend. The birth of Palkia was what caused the walls of our world to disappear, creating a sky that spans for infinity.
name: Palkia

description: Stories tell of this Pokémon being birthed from the boiling magma within Mount Coronet. Its molten-steel body holds many mysteries.
name: Heatran

description: According to legend, Regigigas pulled landmasses together and bound them with rope to create the continent of Hisui. Though I have my doubts, the story could well contain a shred of truth.
name: Regigigas

description: There is one Hisuian verse that tells of a powerful light creating a deep shadow. I imagine that this deep shadow is Giratina.
name: Giratina

description: Cresselia is reminiscent of the crescent moon. It leaves a brilliant line of light in its wake as it flies across the night sky. I daresay it resembles the heavenly maiden who created the Milky Way.
name: Cresselia

description: Can be seen floating offshore during seasons when the seas are warm. Its azure body blends in with the ocean waters—logic suggests this is a defense mechanism against natural predators.
name: Phione

description: Rumored to migrate across the oceans and visit Hisui’s coastal waters only rarely. Although Manaphy resembles Phione, it is also quite different. The relation between the two is unclear.
name: Manaphy

description: On a moonless night, a strange incident occurred in which every one of a village’s inhabitants suffered nightmares. The villagers attested that Darkrai appeared before them in these nightmares.
name: Darkrai

description: When the turning of seasons brings the cruel winter to its end and the joyous people give thanks to the heavens, Shaymin appears and covers the withered land with flowers.
name: Shaymin

description: It is the heavenly fount from which pours the light that shines across Hisui. Its luminance guides and protects all Pokémon. Hisuian mythology states that Arceus is the creator of all things.
name: Arceus

description: When it shares the infinite energy it creates, that being’s entire body will be overflowing with power.
name: Victini

description: They photosynthesize by bathing their tails in sunlight. When they are not feeling well, their tails droop.
name: Snivy

description: When it gets dirty, its leaves can’t be used in photosynthesis, so it always keeps itself clean.
name: Servine

description: It can stop its opponents’ movements with just a glare. It takes in solar energy and boosts it internally.
name: Serperior

description: It loves to eat roasted berries, but sometimes it gets too excited and burns them to a crisp.
name: Tepig

description: When its internal fire flares up, its movements grow sharper and faster. When in trouble, it emits smoke.
name: Pignite

description: It has mastered fast and powerful fighting moves. It grows a beard of fire.
name: Emboar

description: This Pokémon from the Unova region uses the shell on its belly as a weapon to cut down its foes. Thus, I’ve conferred upon this shell the name “scalchop.”
name: Oshawott

description: Its exquisite double-scalchop technique is likely the result of daily training, and it can send even masters of the blade fleeing in defeat.
name: Dewott

description: One swing of the sword incorporated in its armor can fell an opponent. A simple glare from one of them quiets everybody.
name: Samurott

description: Extremely cautious, one of them will always be on the lookout, but it won’t notice a foe coming from behind.
name: Patrat

description: When they see an enemy, their tails stand high, and they spit the seeds of berries stored in their cheek pouches.
name: Watchog

description: This Pokémon is far brighter than the average child, and Lillipup won’t forget the love it receives or any abuse it suffers.
name: Lillipup

description: The black fur that covers this Pokémon’s body is dense and springy. Even sharp fangs bounce right off.
name: Herdier

description: Stoutland is immensely proud of its impressive moustache. It’s said that moustache length is what determines social standing among this species.
name: Stoutland

description: Opponents that get drawn in by its adorable behavior come away with stinging scratches from its claws and stinging pride from its laughter.
name: Purrloin

description: This stealthy Pokémon sneaks up behind prey without making any sound at all. It competes with Thievul for territory.
name: Liepard

description: It’s good at finding berries and gathers them from all over. It’s kind enough to share them with friends.
name: Pansage

description: Ill tempered, it fights by swinging its barbed tail around wildly. The leaf growing on its head is very bitter.
name: Simisage

description: This Pokémon lives in caves in volcanoes. The fire within the tuft on its head can reach 600 degrees Fahrenheit.
name: Pansear

description: When it gets excited, embers rise from its head and tail and it gets hot. For some reason, it loves sweets.
name: Simisear

description: The water stored inside the tuft on its head is full of nutrients. Plants that receive its water grow large.
name: Panpour

description: It prefers places with clean water. When its tuft runs low, it replenishes it by siphoning up water with its tail.
name: Simipour

description: It eats dreams and releases mist. The mist is pink when it’s eating a good dream, and black when it’s eating a nightmare.
name: Munna

description: It drowses and dreams all the time. It’s best to leave it be if it’s just woken up, as it’s a terrible grump when freshly roused from sleep.
name: Musharna

description: It’s forgetful and not very bright, but many Trainers love it anyway for its friendliness and sincerity.
name: Pidove

description: These bright Pokémon have acute memories. Apparently delivery workers often choose them as their partners.
name: Tranquill

description: Males have plumage on their heads. They will never let themselves feel close to anyone other than their Trainers.
name: Unfezant

description: Its mane shines when it discharges electricity. They use the frequency and rhythm of these flashes to communicate.
name: Blitzle

description: They have lightning-like movements. When Zebstrika run at full speed, the sound of thunder reverberates.
name: Zebstrika

description: When it detects a noise, it starts to move. The energy core inside it makes this Pokémon slightly warm to the touch.
name: Roggenrola

description: It relies on sound in order to monitor what’s in its vicinity. When angered, it will attack without ever changing the direction it’s facing.
name: Boldore

description: Although its energy blasts can blow away a dump truck, they have a limitation— they can only be fired when the sun is out.
name: Gigalith

description: It emits ultrasonic waves as it flutters about, searching for its prey—bug Pokémon.
name: Woobat

description: The auspicious shape of this Pokémon’s nose apparently led some regions to consider Swoobat a symbol of good luck.
name: Swoobat

description: It’s a digger, using its claws to burrow through the ground. It causes damage to vegetable crops, so many farmers have little love for it.
name: Drilbur

description: Known as the Drill King, this Pokémon can tunnel through the terrain at speeds of over 90 mph.
name: Excadrill

description: This Pokémon has a kind heart. By touching with its feelers, Audino can gauge other creatures’ feelings and physical conditions.
name: Audino

description: Timburr that have started carrying logs that are about three times their size are nearly ready to evolve.
name: Timburr

description: Gurdurr excels at demolition—construction is not its forte. In any case, there’s skill in the way this Pokémon wields its metal beam.
name: Gurdurr

description: When going all out, this Pokémon throws aside its concrete pillars and leaps at opponents to pummel them with its fists.
name: Conkeldurr

description: It uses sound waves to communicate with others of its kind. People and other Pokémon species can’t hear its cries of warning.
name: Tympole

description: On occasion, their cries are sublimely pleasing to the ear. Palpitoad with larger lumps on their bodies can sing with a wider range of sounds.
name: Palpitoad

description: This Pokémon is popular among the elderly, who say the vibrations of its lumps are great for massages.
name: Seismitoad

description: They train in groups of five. Any member that can’t keep up will discard its belt and leave the group.
name: Throh

description: The karate chops of a Sawk that’s trained itself to the limit can cleave the ocean itself.
name: Sawk

description: Since this Pokémon makes its own clothes out of leaves, it is a popular mascot for fashion designers.
name: Sewaddle

description: It protects itself from the cold by wrapping up in leaves. It stays on the move, eating leaves in forests.
name: Swadloon

description: It keeps its eggs warm with heat from fermenting leaves. It also uses leaves to make warm wrappings for Sewaddle.
name: Leavanny

description: Its fangs are highly venomous. If this Pokémon finds prey it thinks it can eat, it leaps for them without any thought of how things might turn out.
name: Venipede

description: Whirlipede protects itself with a sturdy shell and poisonous spikes while it stores up the energy it’ll need for evolution.
name: Whirlipede

description: Scolipede engage in fierce territorial battles with Centiskorch. At the end of one of these battles, the victor makes a meal of the loser.
name: Scolipede

description: Weaving together the cotton of both Cottonee and Eldegoss produces exquisite cloth that’s highly prized by many luxury brands.
name: Cottonee

description: As long as this Pokémon bathes in sunlight, its cotton keeps growing. If too much cotton fluff builds up, Whimsicott tears it off and scatters it.
name: Whimsicott

description: If the leaves on its head are pruned with regularity, this Pokémon can be grown into a fine plump shape.
name: Petilil

description: No matter how much time and money is spent raising it, its flowers are the most beautiful when they bloom in the wild.
name: Lilligant

description: Red and blue Basculin usually do not get along, but sometimes members of one school mingle with the other’s school.
name: Basculin

description: They live hidden under hot desert sands in order to keep their body temperature from dropping.
name: Sandile

description: Thanks to the special membrane covering its eyes, it can see its surroundings clearly, even in the middle of the night.
name: Krokorok

description: Its unique faculty of sight can detect small prey more than 30 miles away, even in the midst of a sandstorm.
name: Krookodile

description: This popular symbol of good fortune will never fall over in its sleep, no matter how it’s pushed or pulled.
name: Darumaka
