description: Its internal fire burns at 2,500 degrees Fahrenheit, making enough power that it can destroy a dump truck with one punch.
name: Darmanitan

description: Once each year, this Pokémon scatters its seeds. They’re jam-packed with nutrients, making them a precious food source out in the desert.
name: Maractus

description: It first tries to find a rock to live in, but if there are no suitable rocks to be found, Dwebble may move in to the ports of a Hippowdon.
name: Dwebble

description: Its thick claws are its greatest weapons. They’re mighty enough to crack Rhyperior’s carapace.
name: Crustle

description: It protects itself with its durable skin. It’s thought that this Pokémon will evolve once its skin has completely stretched out.
name: Scraggy

description: While mostly known for having the temperament of an aggressive ruffian, this Pokémon takes very good care of its family, friends, and territory.
name: Scrafty

description: A discovery was made in the desert where Sigilyph fly. The ruins of what may have been an ancient city were found beneath the sands.
name: Sigilyph

description: The spirit of a person from a bygone age became this Pokémon. It rambles through ruins, searching for someone who knows its face.
name: Yamask

description: There are many depictions of Cofagrigus decorating ancient tombs. They’re symbols of the wealth that kings of bygone eras had.
name: Cofagrigus

description: Tirtouga is considered to be the ancestor of many turtle Pokémon. It was restored to life from a fossil.
name: Tirtouga

description: This Pokémon emerges from the water in search of prey despite the fact that it moves more slowly on land.
name: Carracosta

description: Archen is said to be the ancestor of bird Pokémon. It lived in treetops, eating berries and bug Pokémon.
name: Archen

description: Though capable of flight, Archeops was apparently better at hunting on the ground.
name: Archeops

description: This Pokémon was born from a bag stuffed with trash. Galarian Weezing relish the fumes belched by Trubbish.
name: Trubbish

description: The toxic liquid it launches from its right arm is so virulent that it can kill a weakened creature instantly.
name: Garbodor

description: To protect themselves from danger, they hide their true identities by transforming into people and Pokémon.
name: Zorua

description: Each has the ability to fool a large group of people simultaneously. They protect their lair with illusory scenery.
name: Zoroark

description: They pet each other with their tails as a form of greeting. Of the two, the one whose tail is fluffier is a bit more boastful.
name: Minccino

description: A special oil that seeps through their fur helps them avoid attacks. The oil fetches a high price at market.
name: Cinccino

description: Beware of touching the ribbon-shaped feelers that control its psychic power. Gothita will begin bawling if you do.
name: Gothita

description: Using its psychic power, it arranges pebbles to form the shapes of constellations. Some people believe this Pokémon came from outer space.
name: Gothorita

description: It gazes at the stars to predict the future. It acts somewhat detached because it has seen the end of all existence.
name: Gothitelle

description: Many say that the special liquid covering this Pokémon’s body would allow it to survive in the vacuum of space.
name: Solosis

description: Its brain has split into two, and the two halves rarely think alike. Its actions are utterly unpredictable.
name: Duosion

description: It’s said that drinking the liquid surrounding Reuniclus grants wisdom. Problem is, the liquid is highly toxic to anything besides Reuniclus itself.
name: Reuniclus

description: They are better at swimming than flying, and they happily eat their favorite food, peat moss, as they dive underwater.
name: Ducklett

description: Swanna start to dance at dusk. The one dancing in the middle is the leader of the flock.
name: Swanna

description: Supposedly, this Pokémon was born from an icicle. It spews out freezing air at −58 degrees Fahrenheit to make itself more comfortable.
name: Vanillite

description: It blasts enemies with cold air reaching −148 degrees Fahrenheit, freezing them solid. But it spares their lives afterward—it’s a kind Pokémon.
name: Vanillish

description: People believe this Pokémon formed when two Vanillish stuck together. Its body temperature is roughly 21 degrees Fahrenheit.
name: Vanilluxe

description: The turning of the seasons changes the color and scent of this Pokémon’s fur. People use it to mark the seasons.
name: Deerling

description: They migrate according to the seasons, so some people call Sawsbuck the harbingers of spring.
name: Sawsbuck

description: This Pokémon absolutely loves sweet berries. Sometimes it stuffs its cheeks full of so much food that it can’t fly properly.
name: Emolga

description: It spits a liquid from its mouth to melt through Shelmet’s shell. Karrablast doesn’t eat the shell— it eats only the contents.
name: Karrablast

description: It charges its enemies, lances at the ready. An image of one of its duels is captured in a famous painting of Escavalier clashing with Sirfetch’d.
name: Escavalier

description: This Pokémon prefers damp places. It spurts out poison spores to repel approaching enemies.
name: Foongus

description: Amoonguss mimics Poké Balls. It is not yet clear whether this mimicry is effective against other Pokémon.
name: Amoonguss

description: Using the invisible poison spikes on its veillike arms and legs, it paralyzes its enemies and causes them to drown.
name: Frillish

description: Fishermen are terrified of Jellicent. It’s rumored to drag them into the sea and steal their lives away.
name: Jellicent

description: They float upon the open sea. Many water Pokémon gather in the area around Alomomola.
name: Alomomola

description: Joltik latch on to other Pokémon and suck out static electricity. They’re often found sticking to Yamper’s hindquarters.
name: Joltik

description: It lays traps of electrified threads near the nests of bird Pokémon, aiming to snare chicks that are not yet good at flying.
name: Galvantula

description: Mossy caves are their preferred dwellings. Enzymes contained in mosses help Ferroseed’s spikes grow big and strong.
name: Ferroseed

description: Its spikes are harder than steel. This Pokémon crawls across rock walls by stabbing the spikes on its feelers into the stone.
name: Ferrothorn

description: It’s suspected that Klink were the inspiration behind ancient people’s invention of the first gears.
name: Klink

description: Many companies in the Galar region choose Klang as their logo. This Pokémon is considered the symbol of industrial technology.
name: Klang

description: The three gears that compose this Pokémon spin at high speed. Its new spiked gear isn’t a living creature.
name: Klinklang

description: These Pokémon move in schools. They have an electricity-generating organ, so they discharge electricity if in danger.
name: Tynamo

description: These Pokémon have a big appetite. When they spot their prey, they attack it and paralyze it with electricity.
name: Eelektrik

description: It latches on to prey with its sucker mouth, sinking in its fangs and shocking the prey with powerful electricity.
name: Eelektross

description: This Pokémon was discovered about 50 years ago. Its highly developed brain enables it to exert its psychic powers.
name: Elgyem

description: Sometimes found drifting above wheat fields, this Pokémon can control the memories of its opponents.
name: Beheeyem

description: The younger the life this Pokémon absorbs, the brighter and eerier the flame on its head burns.
name: Litwick

description: It lurks in cities, pretending to be a lamp. Once it finds someone whose death is near, it will trail quietly after them.
name: Lampent

description: In homes illuminated by Chandelure instead of lights, funerals were a constant occurrence— or so it’s said.
name: Chandelure

description: If you see peculiar teeth marks on boulders or trees, it means an Axew is likely living nearby.
name: Axew

description: Fraxure uses its thick tusks to neatly cut prey into two portions—one to eat now and one to save for later.
name: Fraxure

description: It overwhelms enemies with its prized tusks, which are sharp enough to cut through a metal transmission tower in one strike.
name: Haxorus

description: When Cubchoo starts sneezing, watch out! If it spatters you with its frosty snot, you’ll get frostbite.
name: Cubchoo

description: Feared as the Snow-White Demon in northern lands, Beartic uses its frosty claws and fangs to attack prey.
name: Beartic

description: Cryogonal uses its chains of ice to constrict its opponents and then flash-freezes them where they stand.
name: Cryogonal

description: It has a strange physiology that responds to electricity. When together with Karrablast, Shelmet evolves for some reason.
name: Shelmet

description: Discarding its shell made it nimble. To keep itself from dehydrating, it wraps its body in bands of membrane.
name: Accelgor

description: For some reason, this Pokémon smiles slightly when it emits a strong electric current from the yellow markings on its body.
name: Stunfisk

description: Though small, Mienfoo’s temperament is fierce. Any creature that approaches Mienfoo carelessly will be greeted with a flurry of graceful attacks.
name: Mienfoo

description: Delivered at blinding speeds, kicks from this Pokémon can shatter massive boulders into tiny pieces.
name: Mienshao

description: Druddigon are vicious and cunning. They take up residence in nests dug out by other Pokémon, treating the stolen nests as their own lairs.
name: Druddigon

description: This Pokémon was created from clay. It received orders from its master many thousands of years ago, and it still follows those orders to this day.
name: Golett

description: There’s a theory that inside Golurk is a perpetual motion machine that produces limitless energy, but this belief hasn’t been proven.
name: Golurk

description: Any chips in its blades would prove fatal for it. After each battle, it diligently maintains its blades using its favorite sharpening stone.
name: Pawniard

description: Bisharp mercilessly cuts its opponents to pieces with the sharp blades covering its body. It will do anything to win.
name: Bisharp

description: These Pokémon live in herds of about 20 individuals. Bouffalant that betray the herd will lose the hair on their heads for some reason.
name: Bouffalant

description: With its sharp claws, this Pokémon pierces its prey, and then it pecks at them. Although it also consumes berries, it’s a carnivore at heart.
name: Rufflet

description: For the sake of its friends, this brave warrior of the sky will not stop battling, even if injured.
name: Braviary

description: Vullaby grow quickly. Bones that have gotten too small for older Vullaby to wear often get passed down to younger ones in the nest.
name: Vullaby

description: They adorn themselves with bones. There seem to be fashion trends among them, as different bones come into and fall out of popularity.
name: Mandibuzz

description: A flame serves as its tongue, melting through the hard shell of Durant so that Heatmor can devour their insides.
name: Heatmor

description: With their large mandibles, these Pokémon can crunch their way through rock. They work together to protect their eggs from Sandaconda.
name: Durant

description: It nests deep inside a cave. Food there is scarce, so Deino will sink its teeth into anything that moves and attempt to eat it.
name: Deino

description: The two heads have different likes and dislikes. Because the heads fight with each other, Zweilous gets stronger without needing to rely on others.
name: Zweilous

description: It’s said that Hydreigon grew ferocious because people in times long past loathed it, considering it to be evil incarnate and attacking it relentlessly.
name: Hydreigon

description: In ancient times, Larvesta was worshiped as the emissary of the sun. However, it was also viewed as a burden since it often caused forest fires.
name: Larvesta

description: This Pokémon scatters burning scales. Most of the danger of these scales is not in their heat—it’s in the way they rob the surrounding air of oxygen.
name: Volcarona

description: From the moment it’s born, this Pokémon radiates the air of a leader. Its presence will calm even vicious foes.
name: Cobalion

description: In Unovan legend, Terrakion battled against humans in an effort to protect other Pokémon.
name: Terrakion

description: It darts around opponents with a flurry of quick movements, slicing them up with its horns.
name: Virizion

description: This storm-stirring Pokémon is said to cause the seasons to turn by whipping up the air. I suspect its humanlike form to be a false one.
name: Tornadus

description: They say this wielder of electricity has waged war with its nemesis, Tornadus, since time immemorial. The lightning bolts it hurls pierce the very earth and enrich the soil.
name: Thundurus

description: According to myth, if people ignore truth and let themselves become consumed by greed, Reshiram will arrive to burn their kingdoms down.
name: Reshiram

description: Mythology tells us that if people lose the righteousness in their hearts, their kingdoms will be razed by Zekrom’s lightning.
name: Zekrom

description: When the incarnations of wind and of lightning clash, Landorus arrives to quell the conflict. After the tempests and thunderbolts abate, the land is sure to be blessed with bountiful harvests.
name: Landorus

description: It appears that this Pokémon uses its powers over ice to freeze its own body in order to stabilize its cellular structure.
name: Kyurem

description: When it is resolute, its body fills with power and it becomes swifter. Its jumps are then too fast to follow.
name: Keldeo

description: Its melodies are sung with a special vocalization method that can control the feelings of those who hear it.
name: Meloetta

description: This Pokémon existed 300 million years ago. Team Plasma altered it and attached a cannon to its back.
name: Genesect

description: Such a thick shell of wood covers its head and back that even a direct hit from a truck wouldn’t faze it.
name: Chespin

description: They strengthen their lower bodies by running into one another. They are very kind and won’t start fights.
name: Quilladin

description: When it takes a defensive posture with its fists guarding its face, it could withstand a bomb blast.
name: Chesnaught

description: As it walks, it munches on a twig in place of a snack. It intimidates opponents by puffing hot air out of its ears.
name: Fennekin

description: When the twig is plucked from its tail, friction sets the twig alight. The flame is used to send signals to its allies.
name: Braixen

description: Using psychic power, it generates a fiery vortex of 5,400 degrees Fahrenheit, incinerating foes swept into this whirl of flame.
name: Delphox

description: It protects its skin by covering its body in delicate bubbles. Beneath its happy-go-lucky air, it keeps a watchful eye on its surroundings.
name: Froakie

description: Its swiftness is unparalleled. It can scale a tower of more than 2,000 feet in a minute’s time.
name: Frogadier

description: It appears and vanishes with a ninja’s grace. It toys with its enemies using swift movements, while slicing them with throwing stars of sharpest water.
name: Greninja

description: It’s very sensitive to danger. The sound of Corviknight’s flapping will have Bunnelby digging a hole to hide underground in moments.
name: Bunnelby

description: The fur on its belly retains heat exceptionally well. People used to make heavy winter clothing from fur shed by this Pokémon.
name: Diggersby

description: Fletchling can be found in both rural and urban areas. They once had a huge territorial dispute with Squawkabilly. Fights broke out all over town.
name: Fletchling

description: Its territory has a radius of just over a mile. If any bird Pokémon should enter, it will show them no mercy.
name: Fletchinder

description: When it gets excited, it vents sparks from the gaps between its feathers. These unburnable feathers are used as a fireproof material.
name: Talonflame

description: This Pokémon scatters poisonous powder to repel enemies. It will eat different plants depending on where it lives.
name: Scatterbug

description: Spewpa doesn’t live in a fixed location. It roams where it pleases across the fields and mountains, building up the energy it needs to evolve.
name: Spewpa

description: This Pokémon was born in a land where flowers bloom. It scatters colorful, toxic scales from its wings during battle.
name: Vivillon

description: The more a Litleo trains its body and spirit by battling mighty enemies, the hotter its mane will grow.
name: Litleo

description: The mane of a male Pyroar heats up to over 3,600 degrees Fahrenheit during battle. Merely approaching it will cause severe burns.
name: Pyroar

description: Flabébé wears a crown made from pollen it’s collected from its flower. The crown has hidden healing properties.
name: Flabébé

description: It gives its own power to flowers, pouring its heart into caring for them. Floette never forgives anyone who messes up a flower bed.
name: Floette

description: Its life can span several hundred years. It’s said to devote its entire life to protecting gardens.
name: Florges

description: As long as it has sunlight and water, Skiddo can make energy with the leaves on its body, allowing it to live on rocky mountains barren of food.
name: Skiddo

description: These Pokémon live in herds in mountainous places. The victor in their contests of clashing horns will become the leader of the herd.
name: Gogoat

description: Wanting to make sure it’s taken seriously, Pancham’s always giving others a glare. But if it’s not focusing, it ends up smiling.
name: Pancham

description: Using its leaf, Pangoro can predict the moves of its opponents. It strikes with punches that can turn a dump truck into scrap with just one hit.
name: Pangoro

description: Left alone, its fur will grow longer and longer, but it will only allow someone it trusts to cut it.
name: Furfrou

description: There’s enough psychic power in Espurr to send a wrestler flying, but because this power can’t be controlled, Espurr finds it troublesome.
name: Espurr

description: The eyeball patterns on the interior of its ears emit psychic energy. It keeps the patterns tightly covered because that power is too immense.
name: Meowstic

description: The blue eye on the sword’s handguard is the true body of Honedge. With its old cloth, it drains people’s lives away.
name: Honedge

description: The two swords employ a strategy of rapidly alternating between offense and defense to bring down their prey.
name: Doublade

description: Apparently, it can detect the innate qualities of leadership. According to legend, whoever it recognizes is destined to become king.
name: Aegislash

description: The scent its body gives off enraptures those who smell it. Noble ladies had no shortage of love for Spritzee.
name: Spritzee

description: The scents Aromatisse can produce range from sweet smells that bolster allies to foul smells that sap an opponent’s will to fight.
name: Aromatisse

description: The sweet smell of cotton candy perfumes Swirlix’s fluffy fur. This Pokémon spits out sticky string to tangle up its enemies.
name: Swirlix

description: Slurpuff’s fur contains a lot of air, making it soft to the touch and lighter than it looks.
name: Slurpuff

description: By exposing foes to the blinking of its luminescent spots, Inkay demoralizes them, and then it seizes the chance to flee.
name: Inkay

description: It’s said that Malamar’s hypnotic powers played a role in certain history-changing events.
name: Malamar

description: If the two don’t work well together, both their offense and defense fall apart. Without good teamwork, they won’t survive.
name: Binacle

description: Having an eye on each palm allows it to keep watch in all directions. In a pinch, its limbs start to act on their own to ensure the enemy’s defeat.
name: Barbaracle

description: This Pokémon is a poor swimmer. If it’s caught in a fierce storm, it will sometimes get washed far away and become unable to return to its home.
name: Skrelp

description: Since Finizen is the better swimmer, Dragalge will approach it under the cover of seaweed, then immobilize it with a poisonous attack.
name: Dragalge

description: Clauncher’s claws will regrow if they fall off. The meat inside the claws is edible, but it has a distinct flavor that doesn’t appeal to all tastes.
name: Clauncher

description: The cannonballs of seawater that Clawitzer launches from its claw are powerful enough to punch through tanker hulls.
name: Clawitzer

description: The sun powers this Pokémon’s electricity generation. Interruption of that process stresses Helioptile to the point of weakness.
name: Helioptile

description: One Heliolisk basking in the sun with its frill outspread is all it would take to produce enough electricity to power a city.
name: Heliolisk

description: This Pokémon is selfish and likes to be pampered. It can also inflict grievous wounds on its Trainer just by playing around.
name: Tyrunt

description: A single bite of Tyrantrum’s massive jaws will demolish a car. This Pokémon was the king of the ancient world.
name: Tyrantrum

description: Amaura is an ancient Pokémon that has gone extinct. Specimens of this species can sometimes be found frozen in ice.
name: Amaura

description: When gripped by rage, Aurorus will emanate freezing air, covering everything around it in ice.
name: Aurorus

description: Sylveon cuts an elegant figure as it dances lightly around, feelers fluttering, but its piercing moves aim straight for its opponents’ weak spots.
name: Sylveon

description: Hawlucha live quietly without flocking together. They fight constantly with their natural enemies: noisy groups of Primeape.
name: Hawlucha

description: Dedenne emit electrical waves from the whiskers on their cheeks to communicate with each other. When low on electricity, they curl up and sleep.
name: Dedenne

description: It’s said that somewhere in the world, there’s a mineral vein housing a large pack of slumbering Carbink. It’s also said that this pack has a queen.
name: Carbink

description: Goomy’s horns are excellent sensory organs that cover all five of Goomy’s senses. Goomy picks up on danger from the movement of the air.
name: Goomy

description: When Sliggoo senses danger, the mucus coating its entire body becomes more concentrated—it’ll dissolve anything.
name: Sliggoo

description: This Pokémon is uncontrollable when enraged. It rampages on and on, lashing its tail with enough power to send a dump truck flying.
name: Goodra

description: In the past, noble families entrusted their vault keys to a Klefki. They passed the Klefki down through the generations, taking good care of it.
name: Klefki

description: With a voice like a human child’s, it cries out to lure adults deep into the forest, getting them lost among the trees.
name: Phantump

description: Small roots that extend from the tips of this Pokémon’s feet can tie into the trees of the forest and give Trevenant control over them.
name: Trevenant

description: It is said to carry wandering spirits to the place where they belong so they can move on.
name: Pumpkaboo

description: It enwraps its prey in its hairlike arms. It sings joyfully as it observes the suffering of its prey.
name: Gourgeist

description: Bergmite protects itself by coating its body in ice formed by frigid air of −148 degrees Fahrenheit. It fights with Frigibax whenever they meet.
name: Bergmite

description: This Pokémon uses its massive icy body to flatten anything that gets in its way. When it’s floating out on the ocean, it looks exactly like drift ice.
name: Avalugg

description: Noibat can change the frequency of its sound waves at will, and it generates ultrasonic waves of up to 200,000 hertz.
name: Noibat

description: In the dark, even Hydreigon are terrified of this Pokémon. But in the light, Noivern is the one that avoids battle.
name: Noivern

description: When the horns on its head shine in seven colors, it is said to be sharing everlasting life.
name: Xerneas

description: When its life comes to an end, it absorbs the life energy of every living thing and turns into a cocoon once more.
name: Yveltal

description: Some say it can change to an even more powerful form when battling those who threaten the ecosystem.
name: Zygarde

description: It can instantly create many diamonds by compressing the carbon in the air between its hands.
name: Diancie

description: It is said to be able to seize anything it desires with its six rings and six huge arms. With its power sealed, it is transformed into a much smaller form.
name: Hoopa

description: It expels its internal steam from the arms on its back. It has enough power to blow away a mountain.
name: Volcanion

description: Flies noiselessly on delicate wings. It has mastered the art of deftly launching dagger-sharp feathers from those same wings.
name: Rowlet

description: Regularly basks in sunlight to gather power—presumably due to the frigid climate. Nonetheless, the edges of the blade quills set into its wings are keen as ever.
name: Dartrix

description: In a tenth of a second, it can nock and fire an arrow quill, piercing an opponent’s weak point before they notice what’s happening.
name: Decidueye

description: Trying to pet Litten before it trusts you will result in a nasty scratch from its sharp claws. Be careful.
name: Litten

description: When facing a powerful enemy, Torracat’s fighting spirit gets pumped up, and its fire bell blazes hotter.
name: Torracat

description: Incineroar’s rough and aggressive behavior is its most notable trait, but the way it helps out small Pokémon shows that it has a kind side as well.
name: Incineroar

description: If Popplio want to create big, powerful balloons, they must be persistent. It takes daily practice for these Pokémon to develop their skills.
name: Popplio

description: On nights when the sea is calm, Brionne dance with one another to the singing of the Primarina that’s leading them.
name: Brionne

description: For Primarina, every battle’s a stage. Its singing and the dancing of its balloons will mesmerize the audience.
name: Primarina

description: It may look spindly, but its neck muscles are heavy-duty. It can peck at a tree 16 times per second!
name: Pikipek

description: From its mouth, it fires the seeds of berries it has eaten. The scattered seeds give rise to new plants.
name: Trumbeak

description: Known for forming harmonious couples, this Pokémon is brought to wedding ceremonies as a good luck charm.
name: Toucannon

description: It spends its waking hours searching endlessly for food. When Yungoos is hungry, its ferocity gains a certain edge.
name: Yungoos

description: Gumshoos specializes in relentlessly tracking down prey. The simple-minded Skwovet doesn’t seem to provide Gumshoos enough challenge.
name: Gumshoos

description: It uses its big jaws to dig nests into the forest floor, and it loves to feed on sweet tree sap.
name: Grubbin

description: Its digestive processes convert the leaves it eats into electricity. An electric sac in its belly stores the electricity for later use.
name: Charjabug

description: If it carries a Charjabug to use as a spare battery, a flying Vikavolt can rapidly fire high-powered beams of electricity.
name: Vikavolt

description: If it loses its pincers, they’ll quickly regrow. The pincers are popular ingredients in paella since their shells produce a tasty soup stock.
name: Crabrawler

description: Though its punches are powerful, this Pokémon’s movements are sluggish. It blows icy bubbles from its mouth to immobilize its opponents.
name: Crabominable

description: This form of Oricorio has sipped red nectar. It whips up blazing flames as it moves to the steps of its passionate dance.
name: Oricorio

description: An opponent’s aura can tell Cutiefly what that opponent’s next move will be. Then Cutiefly can glide around the attack and strike back.
name: Cutiefly

description: Ribombee absolutely hate getting wet or rained on. In the cloudy Galar region, they are very seldom seen.
name: Ribombee

description: This Pokémon travels in a pack with others until it grows up. When its mood turns sour, it starts striking the ground with the rocks on its neck.
name: Rockruff

description: It has a calm and collected demeanor. It swiftly closes in on its prey, then slices them with the rocks in its mane.
name: Lycanroc

description: When it senses danger, its eyes tear up. The sparkle of its tears signals other Wishiwashi to gather.
name: Wishiwashi

description: It has excellent regenerative capabilities. Legs that a Mareanie has lost have a very bitter, astringent flavor—they’re not suitable as food.
name: Mareanie

description: Toxapex gets into fierce battles with Bruxish over areas where warm ocean currents flow, but the odds are always against it.
name: Toxapex

description: Though a slow walker, Mudbray is plenty strong. Its pace doesn’t change even when it’s loaded with 50 times its own body weight.
name: Mudbray

description: Its legs are fortified with mud and harder than stone, and they can reduce a large truck to scrap with one kick.
name: Mudsdale

description: Dewpider normally lives underwater. When it comes onto land in search of food, it takes water with it in the form of a bubble on its head.
name: Dewpider

description: It acts as a caretaker for Dewpider, putting them inside its bubble and letting them eat any leftover food.
name: Araquanid

description: Many Trainers give their Fomantis their own flowerpots so they can sunbathe in peace and quiet.
name: Fomantis

description: A lot of time and effort is required to maintain the vivid colors of its petals. This Pokémon puts its Trainer’s attentiveness to the test.
name: Lurantis

description: Morelull live in forests that stay dark even during the day. They scatter flickering spores that put enemies to sleep.
name: Morelull

description: If you see a light deep in a forest at night, don’t go near. Shiinotic will make you fall fast asleep.
name: Shiinotic

description: Only female Salandit can produce gas laden with pheromones. Males entranced by this gas will do whatever the females tell them.
name: Salandit

description: When two Salazzle meet, they will use their pheromone gas to fight over the males in each other’s group.
name: Salazzle

description: The way it protects itself by flailing its arms may be an adorable sight, but stay well away. This is flailing that can snap thick tree trunks.
name: Stufful

description: The moves it uses to take down its prey would make a martial artist jealous. It tucks subdued prey under its arms to carry them to its nest.
name: Bewear

description: A Greedent drawn in by the sweet scent of these Pokémon will tuck the Bounsweet in among the berries in its tail and carry them all away.
name: Bounsweet

description: Steenee bounces energetically through forests. If the rind that peels off its body is pulverized, it can be used to treat stomach pains.
name: Steenee

description: This Pokémon launches fierce yet elegant kicks with its long, slender legs. It views Quaquaval as its rival.
name: Tsareena

description: These Pokémon smell very nice. All Comfey wear different flowers, so each of these Pokémon has its own individual scent.
name: Comfey

description: This Pokémon lives quietly in the depths of the forest. The purple, cape-like fur gets longer and longer as Oranguru ages.
name: Oranguru

description: The boss chooses 10 members of the group to go out hunting. The hunting party will evenly split the food they find with the rest of the group.
name: Passimian

description: Wimpod gather in swarms, constantly on the lookout for danger. They scatter the moment they detect an enemy’s presence.
name: Wimpod

description: They live in sunken ships or in holes in the seabed. When Golisopod and Grapploct battle, the loser becomes the winner’s meal.
name: Golisopod

description: It flings sand into the eyes of its prey and tries to close in on them while they’re blinded, but since Sandygast is so slow, the prey tends to escape.
name: Sandygast

description: From the hollows in its arms, it fires the bones of its victims, which are all dried up after being drained of their vitality.
name: Palossand

description: It’s covered in a slime that keeps its skin moist, allowing it to stay on land for days without drying up.
name: Pyukumuku

description: It was modeled after a mighty Pokémon of myth. The mask placed upon it limits its power in order to keep it under control.
name: Type: Null

description: The final factor needed to release this Pokémon’s true power was a strong bond with a Trainer it trusts.
name: Silvally

description: Although its outer shell is uncommonly durable, the shock of falling to the ground smashes the shell to smithereens.
name: Minior

description: A potent anesthetic can be made by diluting Komala’s drool. This anesthetic was used for surgeries in the past.
name: Komala

description: Eating sulfur in its volcanic habitat is what causes explosive compounds to develop in its shell. Its droppings are also dangerously explosive.
name: Turtonator

description: When it’s in trouble, it curls up into a ball, makes its fur spikes stand on end, and then discharges electricity indiscriminately.
name: Togedemaru

description: Mimikyu was only recently identified as a Pokémon. Previously, people thought it was just a ghost wearing a cloth.
name: Mimikyu

description: When sunlight reflects on the ripples created by a Bruxish grinding its teeth, the water all around sparkles brilliantly.
name: Bruxish

description: Drampa is a kind and friendly Pokémon—up until it’s angered. When that happens, it stirs up a gale and flattens everything around.
name: Drampa

description: After lowering its anchor, it waits for its prey. It catches large Wailord and drains their life-force.
name: Dhelmise

description: Jangmo-o strikes its scales to communicate with others of its kind. Its scales are actually fur that’s become as hard as metal.
name: Jangmo-o

description: Before attacking its enemies, it clashes its scales together and roars. Its sharp claws shred the opposition.
name: Hakamo-o

description: Certain ruins have paintings of ancient warriors wearing armor made of Kommo-o scales.
name: Kommo-o

description: The lightning-wielding guardian deity of Melemele, Tapu Koko is brimming with curiosity and appears before people from time to time.
name: Tapu Koko

description: Although called a guardian deity, Tapu Lele is devoid of guilt about its cruel disposition and can be described as nature incarnate.
name: Tapu Lele

description: It makes ringing sounds with its tail to let others know where it is, avoiding unneeded conflicts. This guardian deity of Ula’ula controls plants.
name: Tapu Bulu

description: Although it’s called a guardian deity, terrible calamities sometimes befall those who recklessly approach Tapu Fini.
name: Tapu Fini

description: Cosmog is very curious but not very cautious, often placing itself in danger. If things start to look dicey, it teleports away.
name: Cosmog

description: It sucks in dust from the air at an astounding rate, frantically building up energy within its core as preparation for evolution.
name: Cosmoem

description: Solgaleo was once known as the Beast That Devours the Sun. Energy in the form of light radiates boundlessly from it.
name: Solgaleo

description: It steals the light from its surroundings and then becomes the full moon, showering its own light across the night sky.
name: Lunala

description: It appeared in this world from an Ultra Wormhole. Nihilego appears to be a parasite that lives by feeding on people and Pokémon.
name: Nihilego

description: Buzzwole goes around showing off its abnormally swollen muscles. It is one kind of Ultra Beast.
name: Buzzwole

description: Although it’s alien to this world and a danger here, it’s apparently a common organism in the world where it normally lives.
name: Pheromosa

description: They’ve been dubbed Ultra Beasts. Some of them stand unmoving, like trees, with their arms and legs stuck into the ground.
name: Xurkitree

description: Although it’s alien to this world and a danger here, it’s apparently a common organism in the world where it normally lives.
name: Celesteela

description: Although it’s alien to this world and a danger here, it’s apparently a common organism in the world where it normally lives.
name: Kartana

description: An unknown life-form called a UB. It may be constantly hungry—it is certainly always devouring something.
name: Guzzlord

description: It needs light to survive, and it goes on a rampage seeking it out. Its laser beams will cut anything to pieces.
name: Necrozma

description: Built roughly 500 years ago by a scientist, the part called the Soul-Heart is the actual life-form.
name: Magearna

description: This Pokémon can conceal itself in any shadow, so it went undiscovered for a long time.
name: Marshadow

description: An Ultra Beast that lives in a different world, it cackles wildly as it sprays its opponents with poison from the needles on its head.
name: Poipole

description: One kind of Ultra Beast, it fires a glowing, venomous liquid from its needles. This liquid is also immensely adhesive.
name: Naganadel

description: When stone walls started moving and attacking, the brute’s true identity was this mysterious life-form, which brings to mind an Ultra Beast.
name: Stakataka

description: A UB that appeared from an Ultra Wormhole, it causes explosions, then takes advantage of opponents’ surprise to rob them of their vitality.
name: Blacephalon

description: Electricity sparks from the pads on its limbs. Wherever Zeraora runs, lightning flashes and thunder echoes.
name: Zeraora

description: They live as a group, but when the time comes, one strong Meltan will absorb all the others and evolve.
name: Meltan

description: Centrifugal force is behind the punches of Melmetal’s heavy hex-nut arms. Melmetal is said to deliver the strongest punches of all Pokémon.
name: Melmetal

description: It attacks with rapid beats of its stick. As it strikes with amazing speed, it gets more and more pumped.
name: Grookey

description: When it’s drumming out rapid beats in battle, it gets so caught up in the rhythm that it won’t even notice that it’s already knocked out its opponent.
name: Thwackey

description: The one with the best drumming techniques becomes the boss of the troop. It has a gentle disposition and values harmony among its group.
name: Rillaboom

description: It has special pads on the backs of its feet, and one on its nose. Once it’s raring to fight, these pads radiate tremendous heat.
name: Scorbunny

description: It kicks berries right off the branches of trees and then juggles them with its feet, practicing its footwork.
name: Raboot

description: It’s skilled at both offense and defense, and it gets pumped up when cheered on. But if it starts showboating, it could put itself in a tough spot.
name: Cinderace

description: When it gets wet, its skin changes color, and this Pokémon becomes invisible as if it were camouflaged.
name: Sobble

description: Highly intelligent but also very lazy, it keeps enemies out of its territory by laying traps everywhere.
name: Drizzile

description: Its nictitating membranes let it pick out foes’ weak points so it can precisely blast them with water that shoots from its fingertips at Mach 3.
name: Inteleon

description: No matter how much it stuffs its belly with food, it is always anxious about getting hungry again. So, it stashes berries in its cheeks and tail.
name: Skwovet

description: This Pokémon makes off with heaps of fallen berries by wrapping them in its tail, which is roughly twice the length of its body.
name: Greedent

description: The females are fussier than the males. If another creature dirties a female Rookidee’s wings, it’ll peck the offender relentlessly in a burning rage.
name: Rookidee

description: This intelligent Pokémon will quickly learn how to use any tool it can hold in its beak or its talons.
name: Corvisquire

description: Although its wings have partly turned to steel and become heavy as a result, this Pokémon flies through the skies with ease.
name: Corviknight

description: Often found in gardens, this Pokémon has hairs on its body that it uses to assess its surroundings.
name: Blipbug

description: As it grows inside its shell, it uses its psychic abilities to monitor the outside world and prepare for evolution.
name: Dottler

description: It emits psychic energy to observe and study what’s around it—and what’s around it can include things over six miles away.
name: Orbeetle

description: Cunning and cautious, this Pokémon survives by stealing food from others. It erases its tracks with swipes of its tail as it makes off with its plunder.
name: Nickit

description: With a lithe body and sharp claws, it goes around stealing food and eggs. Boltund is its natural enemy.
name: Thievul

description: It whirls around in the wind while singing a joyous song. This delightful display has charmed many into raising this Pokémon.
name: Gossifleur

description: The cotton on the head of this Pokémon can be spun into a glossy, gorgeous yarn—a Galar regional specialty.
name: Eldegoss

description: If its fleece grows too long, Wooloo won’t be able to move. Cloth made with the wool of this Pokémon is surprisingly strong.
name: Wooloo

description: Its majestic horns are meant only to impress the opposite gender. They never see use in battle.
name: Dubwool

description: A popular game among children is to lift up sticks that Chewtle have bitten onto to see whose Chewtle can hang on the longest.
name: Chewtle

description: Drednaw lurks along the shoreline. When prey come to drink water, Drednaw stretches its neck out and chomps down on them.
name: Drednaw

description: This gluttonous Pokémon only assists people with their work because it wants treats. As it runs, it crackles with electricity.
name: Yamper

description: It sends electricity through its legs to boost their strength. Running at top speed, it easily breaks 50 mph.
name: Boltund

description: Chunks of the surface of this Pokémon’s body that have grown old and flaked off have long been used for fuel as an alternative to coal.
name: Rolycoly

description: Due to the coal tar created inside it, the heap of coal on Carkol’s back never falls apart, even when the Pokémon rolls around at high speeds.
name: Carkol

description: It’s gentle usually but fearsome when angered. With a body that burns at over 2,700 degrees Fahrenheit, it crushes foes and turns them to ash.
name: Coalossal

description: Applin lives inside an apple. When an Applin is separated from its apple, its body loses moisture and the Pokémon grows weak.
name: Applin

description: It uses its own body fluid to repair its apple. Strong Flapple that have won many battles have apples that are clay colored all over.
name: Flapple

description: When some Lechonk come along to lick the sweet nectar on Appletun’s back, Appletun will spew sticky nectar at them to drive them away.
name: Appletun

description: Silicobra’s large nostrils are specialized for spraying sand, so this Pokémon is not very good at telling apart different smells.
name: Silicobra

description: The sand it spews contains sharp, pointy gravel, which is actually just sand that Sandaconda’s saliva has hardened into irregular shapes.
name: Sandaconda

description: This hungry Pokémon swallows Arrokuda whole. Occasionally, it makes a mistake and tries to swallow a Pokémon other than its preferred prey.
name: Cramorant

description: It takes down prey by charging into them with its hard, pointed jaw. But Arrokuda’s eyesight is poor, so this tactic has a low success rate.
name: Arrokuda

description: It swims at speeds of over 100 knots and battles fiercely with pods of Finizen over prey.
name: Barraskewda

description: This selfish, attention-seeking Pokémon stores poison and electricity in two different sacs inside its body.
name: Toxel

description: As it gulps down stagnant water and generates electricity in its body, a sound like a rhythm played by a bass guitar reverberates all around.
name: Amped Toxtricity

description: It wraps prey up with its heated body, cooking them in its coils. Once they’re well-done, it will voraciously nibble them down to the last morsel.
name: Sizzlipede

description: While its burning body is already dangerous on its own, this excessively hostile Pokémon also has large and very sharp fangs.
name: Centiskorch

description: Its tentacles tear off easily, but it isn’t alarmed when that happens—it knows they’ll grow back. It’s about as smart as a three-year-old.
name: Clobbopus

description: Searching for an opponent to test its skills against, it emerges onto land. Once the battle is over, it returns to the sea.
name: Grapploct

description: Sinistea gets into your body when you drink it, and then it steals your vitality from within. It also tastes awful.
name: Sinistea

description: Though risky to drink, this Pokémon’s tea tastes delicious. Gourmets who have no fear of danger drink Polteageist tea day after day.
name: Polteageist

description: It senses the feelings of other living creatures. Be careful not to expose it to strong emotions for too long, or it will end up exhausted.
name: Hatenna

description: The moment this Pokémon finds someone who’s emitting strong emotions, it will pummel them senseless with its braids to silence them.
name: Hattrem

description: Beware of forests that show no signs of living creatures within. You may have wandered into Hatterene’s territory.
name: Hatterene

description: They live in groups, pestering and playing pranks on each other to polish their troublemaking skills.
name: Impidimp

description: This Pokémon absorbs negative emotions and turns them into energy. It’s popular with people who tend to think gloomy thoughts.
name: Morgrem

description: It lives deep within the forest. Even after evolving into this splendid form, it hasn’t given up on its petty misdeeds and pranks.
name: Grimmsnarl

description: It evolved after experiencing numerous fights. While crossing its arms, it lets out a shout that would make any opponent flinch.
name: Obstagoon

description: After many battles, it evolved dangerous claws that come together to form daggers when extended.
name: Perrserker

description: Be cautious of the ectoplasmic body surrounding its soul. You’ll become stiff as stone if you touch it.
name: Cursola

description: After deflecting attacks with its hard leaf shield, it strikes back with its sharp leek stalk. The leek stalk is both weapon and food.
name: Sirfetch'd

description: Its amusing movements make it very popular. It releases its psychic power from the pattern on its belly.
name: Mr. Rime

description: Never touch its shadowlike body, or you’ll be shown the horrific memories behind the picture carved into it.
name: Runerigus

description: They say that any patisserie visited by Milcery is guaranteed success and good fortune.
name: Milcery

description: Alcremie that have been cherished produce exquisite cream, so Trainers always raise them lovingly.
name: Alcremie

description: The leader, known as the brass, uses its extendible horn to issue orders to the others when it’s time to change formation.
name: Falinks

description: This Pokémon is so timid that even brushing against seaweed will make it discharge electricity in surprise. Its lips do not conduct electricity.
name: Pincurchin

description: Within its internal organs, Snom amplifies the frigid air it gets from eating snow and then uses this amplified air to create icicle-like spikes.
name: Snom

description: It causes blizzards as it flies around with its huge, chill-emanating wings. Clean meltwater is its favorite thing to drink.
name: Frosmoth

description: This Pokémon spends its life gazing at the setting sun. It strides leisurely across grassy plains on legs of rock that weigh over 400 pounds each.
name: Stonjourner

description: If you lick the ice covering its face, you’ll find it has a faintly salty taste. This species rode here on ocean currents from a cold, faraway land.
name: Eiscue

description: This Pokémon never leaves its Trainer’s side. It predicts their actions with its psychic power and takes care of their day-to-day needs.
name: Indeedee

description: It carries electrically roasted seeds with it as if they’re precious treasures. No matter how much it eats, it always gets hungry again in short order.
name: Morpeko

description: Cufant can lift loads weighing five tons. In the mornings, it heads into caves with its herd, in search of the ore on which these Pokémon feed.
name: Cufant

description: Copperajah are prideful, cantankerous Pokémon. Specimens with vibrant green skin command the respect of others of their kind.
name: Copperajah

description: The powerful muscles in its tail generate its electricity. Compared to its lower body, its upper half is entirely too small.
name: Dracozolt

description: This Pokémon lived on prehistoric seashores and was able to preserve food with the ice on its body. It went extinct because it moved so slowly.
name: Arctozolt

description: Its mighty legs are capable of running at speeds exceeding 40 mph, but this Pokémon can’t breathe unless it’s underwater.
name: Dracovish

description: The skin on its face is impervious to attack, but breathing difficulties made this Pokémon go extinct anyway.
name: Arctovish

description: The special metal that composes its body is very light, so this Pokémon has considerable agility. It lives in caves because it dislikes the rain.
name: Duraludon

description: It has a habit of biting at Clauncher even though it doesn’t feed on them. This is said to be vestigial behavior from when Dreepy was alive.
name: Dreepy

description: This Pokémon stores up energy in its lungs, then shoots it out. It takes care of Dreepy and battles alongside them until they’re all grown up.
name: Drakloak

description: The fastest Dragapult of the group is always surrounded by Dreepy that want to fly at sonic speed.
name: Dragapult

description: This Pokémon has slumbered for many years. Some say it’s Zamazenta’s elder sister—others say the two Pokémon are rivals.
name: Zacian

description: This Pokémon slept for aeons while in the form of a statue. It was asleep for so long, people forgot that it ever existed.
name: Zamazenta

description: It was inside a meteorite that fell 20,000 years ago. There seems to be a connection between this Pokémon and the Dynamax phenomenon.
name: Eternatus

description: If Kubfu pulls the long white hair on its head, its fighting spirit heightens and power wells up from the depths of its belly.
name: Kubfu

description: Inhabiting the mountains of a distant region, this Pokémon races across sheer cliffs, training its legs and refining its moves.
name: Urshifu

description: Once the vines on Zarude’s body tear off, they become nutrients in the soil. This helps the plants of the forest grow.
name: Zarude

description: Its entire body is made up of a single organ that generates electrical energy. Regieleki is capable of creating all Galar’s electricity.
name: Regieleki

description: Its body is composed of crystallized dragon energy. Regidrago is said to have the powers of every dragon Pokémon.
name: Regidrago

description: Glastrier has tremendous physical strength, and the mask of ice covering its face is 100 times harder than diamond.
name: Glastrier

description: As it dashes through the night, Spectrier absorbs the life-force of sleeping creatures. It craves silence and solitude.
name: Spectrier

description: Calyrex is known in legend as a king that ruled over Galar in ancient times. It has the power to cause hearts to mend and plants to spring forth.
name: Calyrex

description: The black orbs shine with an uncanny light when the Pokémon is erecting invisible barriers. The fur shed from its beard retains heat well and is a highly useful material for winter clothing.
name: Wyrdeer

description: A violent creature that fells towering trees with its crude axes and shields itself with hard stone. If one should chance upon this Pokémon in the wilds, one’s only recourse is to flee.
name: Kleavor

description: I believe it was Hisui’s swampy terrain that gave Ursaluna its burly physique and newfound capacity to manipulate peat at will.
name: Ursaluna

description: Clads itself in the souls of comrades that perished before fulfilling their goals of journeying upstream. No other species throughout all Hisui’s rivers is Basculegion’s equal.
name: Basculegion

description: Because of Sneasler’s virulent poison and daunting physical prowess, no other species could hope to best it on the frozen highlands. Preferring solitude, this species does not form packs.
name: Sneasler

description: Its lancelike spikes and savage temperament have earned it the nickname “sea fiend.” It slurps up poison to nourish itself.
name: Overqwil

description: When it flies to this land from across the sea, the bitter winter comes to an end. According to legend, this Pokémon’s love gives rise to the budding of fresh life across Hisui.
name: Enamorus

description: The sweet scent its body gives off mesmerizes those around it. The scent grows stronger when this Pokémon is in the sun.
name: Sprigatito

description: The hardness of Floragato’s fur depends on the Pokémon’s mood. When Floragato is prepared to battle, its fur becomes pointed and needle sharp.
name: Floragato

description: With skillful misdirection, it rigs foes with pollen-packed flower bombs. Meowscarada sets off the bombs before its foes realize what’s going on.
name: Meowscarada

description: Its flame sac is small, so energy is always leaking out. This energy is released from the dent atop Fuecoco’s head and flickers to and fro.
name: Fuecoco

description: The valve in Crocalor’s flame sac is closely connected to its vocal cords. This Pokémon utters a guttural cry as it spews flames every which way.
name: Crocalor

description: Skeledirge’s gentle singing soothes the souls of all that hear it. It burns its enemies to a crisp with flames of over 5,400 degrees Fahrenheit.
name: Skeledirge

description: Its strong legs let it easily swim around in even fast-flowing rivers. It likes to keep things tidy and is prone to overthinking things.
name: Quaxly

description: The hardworking Quaxwell observes people and Pokémon from various regions and incorporates their movements into its own dance routines.
name: Quaxwell

description: Dancing in ways that evoke far-away places, this Pokémon mesmerizes all that see it. Flourishes of its decorative water feathers slice into its foes.
name: Quaquaval

description: This Pokémon spurns all but the finest of foods. Its body gives off an herblike scent that bug Pokémon detest.
name: Lechonk

description: It entrances female Pokémon with the sweet, alluring scent that wafts from all over its body.
name: Oinkologne

description: The thread it secretes from its rear is as strong as wire. The secret behind the thread’s strength is the topic of ongoing research.
name: Tarountula

description: Spidops covers its territory in tough, sticky threads to set up traps for intruders.
name: Spidops

description: It’s highly skilled at a fighting style in which it uses its jumping capabilities to dodge incoming attacks while also dealing damage to opponents.
name: Nymble

description: It uses its normally folded third set of legs when in Showdown Mode. This places a huge burden on its body, so it can’t stay in this mode for long.
name: Lokix

description: The pads of its paws are electricity-discharging organs. Pawmi fires electricity from its forepaws while standing unsteadily on its hind legs.
name: Pawmi

description: Pawmo uses a unique fighting technique in which it uses its forepaws to strike foes and zap them with electricity from its paw pads simultaneously.
name: Pawmo

description: Pawmot’s fluffy fur acts as a battery. It can store the same amount of electricity as an electric car.
name: Pawmot

description: The pair sticks together no matter what. They split any food they find exactly in half and then eat it together.
name: Tandemaus

description: The larger pair protects the little ones during battles. When facing strong opponents, the whole group will join the fight.
name: Maushold

description: The yeast in Fidough’s breath is useful for cooking, so this Pokémon has been protected by people since long ago.
name: Fidough

description: The surface of this Pokémon’s skin hardens when exposed to intense heat, and its body has an appetizing aroma.
name: Dachsbun

description: This Pokémon converts nutrients into oil, which it stores in the fruit on its head. It can easily go a whole week without eating or drinking.
name: Smoliv

description: It basks in the sun to its heart’s content until the fruits on its head ripen. After that, Dolliv departs from human settlements and goes on a journey.
name: Dolliv

description: This Pokémon drives back enemies by launching its rich, aromatic oil at them with enough force to smash a boulder.
name: Arboliva

description: Green-feathered flocks hold the most sway. When they’re out searching for food in the mornings and evenings, it gets very noisy.
name: Squawkabilly

description: The ground scrapes its body as it travels, causing it to leave salt behind. Salt is constantly being created and replenished inside Nacli’s body.
name: Nacli

description: It compresses rock salt inside its body and shoots out hardened salt pellets with enough force to perforate an iron sheet.
name: Naclstack

description: Many Pokémon gather around Garganacl, hoping to lick at its mineral-rich salt.
name: Garganacl

description: Its firepower increases when it fights, reaching over 1,800 degrees Fahrenheit. It likes berries that are rich in fat.
name: Charcadet

description: This Pokémon clads itself in armor that has been fortified by psychic and fire energy, and it shoots blazing fireballs.
name: Armarouge

description: An old set of armor steeped in grudges caused this Pokémon’s evolution. Ceruledge cuts its enemies to pieces without mercy.
name: Ceruledge

description: It floats using the electricity stored in its body. When thunderclouds are around, Tadbulb will float higher off the ground.
name: Tadbulb

description: What appear to be eyeballs are actually organs for discharging the electricity generated by Bellibolt’s belly-button dynamo.
name: Bellibolt

description: These Pokémon make their nests on coastal cliffs. The nests have a strange, crackling texture, and they’re a popular delicacy.
name: Wattrel

description: It uses its throat sac to store electricity generated by its wings. There’s hardly any oil in its feathers, so it is a poor swimmer.
name: Kilowattrel

description: Its well-developed jaw and fangs are strong enough to crunch through boulders, and its thick fat makes for an excellent defense.
name: Maschiff

description: Mabosstiff loves playing with children. Though usually gentle, it takes on an intimidating look when protecting its family.
name: Mabosstiff

description: To keep enemies away from its territory, it paints markings around its nest using a poisonous liquid that has an acrid odor.
name: Shroodle

description: Each Grafaiai paints its own individual pattern, and it will paint that same pattern over and over again throughout its life.
name: Grafaiai

description: Not even Bramblin knows where it is headed as it tumbles across the wilderness, blown by the wind. It loathes getting wet.
name: Bramblin

description: Brambleghast wanders around arid regions. On rare occasions, mass outbreaks of these Pokémon will bury an entire town.
name: Brambleghast

description: Though it looks like Tentacool, Toedscool is a completely different species. Its legs may be thin, but it can run at a speed of 30 mph.
name: Toedscool

description: It coils its 10 tentacles around prey and sucks out their nutrients, causing the prey pain. The folds along the rim of its head are a popular delicacy.
name: Toedscruel

description: This Pokémon lives on sheer cliffs. It sidesteps opponents’ attacks, then lunges for their weak spots with its claws.
name: Klawf

description: Traditional Paldean dishes can be extremely spicy because they include the shed front teeth of Capsakid among their ingredients.
name: Capsakid

description: The green head has turned vicious due to the spicy chemicals stimulating its brain. Once it goes on a rampage, there is no stopping it.
name: Scovillain

description: It rolls its mud ball around while the energy it needs for evolution matures. Eventually the time comes for it to evolve.
name: Rellor

description: An infant sleeps inside the ball. Rabsca rolls the ball soothingly with its legs to ensure the infant sleeps comfortably.
name: Rabsca

description: It spends its time running around wastelands. If anyone steals its beloved berries, it will chase them down and exact its revenge.
name: Flittle

description: It emits psychic power from the gaps between its multicolored frills and sprints at speeds greater than 120 mph.
name: Espathra

description: This Pokémon pounds iron scraps together to make a hammer. It will remake the hammer again and again until it’s satisfied with the result.
name: Tinkatink

description: These Pokémon make their homes in piles of scrap metal. They test the strength of each other’s hammers by smashing them together.
name: Tinkatuff

description: The hammer tops 220 pounds, yet it gets swung around easily by Tinkaton as it steals whatever it pleases and carries its plunder back home.
name: Tinkaton

description: Though it looks like Diglett, Wiglett is an entirely different species. The resemblance seems to be a coincidental result of environmental adaptation.
name: Wiglett

description: A variety of fish Pokémon, Wugtrio was once considered to be a regional form of Dugtrio.
name: Wugtrio

description: Bombirdier uses the apron on its chest to bundle up food, which it carries back to its nest. It enjoys dropping things that make loud noises.
name: Bombirdier

description: Its water ring is made from seawater mixed with a sticky fluid that Finizen secretes from its blowhole.
name: Finizen

description: Its physical capabilities are no different than a Finizen’s, but when its allies are in danger, it transforms and powers itself up.
name: Palafin

description: The steel section is Varoom’s actual body. This Pokémon clings to rocks and converts the minerals within into energy to fuel its activities.
name: Varoom

description: Revavroom viciously threatens others with the sound of its exhaust. It sticks its tongue out from its cylindrical mouth and sprays toxic fluids.
name: Revavroom

description: It can sprint at over 70 mph while carrying a human. The rider’s body heat warms Cyclizar’s back and lifts the Pokémon’s spirit.
name: Cyclizar

description: This Pokémon lives in arid deserts. It maintains its metal body by consuming iron from the soil.
name: Orthworm

description: Glimmet’s toxic mineral crystals look just like flower petals. This Pokémon scatters poisonous powder like pollen to protect itself.
name: Glimmet

description: Glimmora’s petals are made of crystallized poison energy. It has recently become evident that these petals resemble Tera Jewels.
name: Glimmora

description: This friendly Pokémon doesn’t like being alone. Pay it even the slightest bit of attention, and it will follow you forever.
name: Greavard

description: A lovingly mourned Pokémon was reborn as Houndstone. It doesn’t like anyone touching the protuberance atop its head.
name: Houndstone

description: Thanks to a behavior of theirs known as “synchronizing,” an entire flock of these Pokémon can attack simultaneously in perfect harmony.
name: Flamigo

description: It lives in frigid regions in pods of five or so individuals. It loves the minerals found in snow and ice.
name: Cetoddle

description: Ice energy builds up in the horn on its upper jaw, causing the horn to reach cryogenic temperatures that freeze its surroundings.
name: Cetitan

description: Veluza has excellent regenerative capabilities. It sheds spare flesh from its body to boost its agility, then charges at its prey.
name: Veluza

description: It treats Tatsugiri like its boss and follows it loyally. Though powerful, Dondozo is apparently not very smart.
name: Dondozo

description: Tatsugiri is an extremely cunning Pokémon. It feigns weakness to lure in prey, then orders its partner to attack.
name: Tatsugiri

description: It imbues its fists with the power of the rage that it kept hidden in its heart. Opponents struck by these imbued fists will be shattered to their core.
name: Annihilape

description: It lives at the bottom of ponds and swamps. It will carry Wooper on its back and ferry them across water from one shore to the other.
name: Clodsire

description: The hardened head from the tail protects the head of the main body as Farigiraf whips its long neck around to headbutt enemies.
name: Farigiraf

description: It drives enemies out of its nest by sucking in enough air to fill its long, narrow lungs, then releasing the air in an intense blast.
name: Dudunsparce

description: Though it commands a massive army in battle, it’s not skilled at devising complex strategies. It just uses brute strength to keep pushing.
name: Kingambit

description: This creature resembles a mysterious Pokémon that, according to a paranormal magazine, has lived since ancient times.
name: Great Tusk

description: It resembles a mysterious Pokémon described in a paranormal magazine as a Jigglypuff from one billion years ago.
name: Scream Tail

description: It bears a slight resemblance to a Pokémon described in a dubious magazine as a cross between a dinosaur and a mushroom.
name: Brute Bonnet

description: It has similar features to a ghostly pterosaur that was covered in a paranormal magazine, but the two have little else in common.
name: Flutter Mane

description: This Pokémon somewhat resembles an ancient form of Volcarona that was introduced in a dubious magazine.
name: Slither Wing

description: It slightly resembles a Magneton that lived for 10,000 years and was featured in an article in a paranormal magazine.
name: Sandy Shocks

description: Sightings of this Pokémon have occurred in recent years. It resembles a mysterious object described in an old expedition journal.
name: Iron Treads

description: It resembles a mysterious object mentioned in an old book. There are only two reported sightings of this Pokémon.
name: Iron Bundle

description: This Pokémon shares many similarities with Iron Hands, an object mentioned in a certain expedition journal.
name: Iron Hands

description: It’s possible that Iron Jugulis, an object described in an old book, may actually be this Pokémon.
name: Iron Jugulis

description: No records exist of this species being caught. Data is lacking, but the Pokémon’s traits match up with an object described in an old book.
name: Iron Moth

description: Some of its notable features match those of an object named within a certain expedition journal as Iron Thorns.
name: Iron Thorns

description: This Pokémon lives in forests and craggy areas. Using the power of its dorsal fin, it cools the inside of its nest like a refrigerator.
name: Frigibax

description: It attacks with the blade of its frozen dorsal fin by doing a front flip in the air. Arctibax’s strong back and legs allow it to pull off this technique.
name: Arctibax

description: It launches itself into battle by flipping upside down and spewing frigid air from its mouth. It finishes opponents off with its dorsal blade.
name: Baxcalibur

description: It lives inside an old treasure chest. Sometimes it gets left in shop corners since no one realizes it’s actually a Pokémon.
name: Gimmighoul

description: It has a sturdy body made up of stacked coins. Gholdengo overwhelms its enemies by firing coin after coin at them in quick succession.
name: Gholdengo

description: It drains the life-force from vegetation, causing nearby forests to instantly wither and fields to turn barren.
name: Wo-Chien

description: The hatred of those who perished by the sword long ago has clad itself in snow and become a Pokémon.
name: Chien-Pao

description: It slowly brings its exceedingly heavy head down upon the ground, splitting the earth open with huge fissures that run over 160 feet deep.
name: Ting-Lu

description: The envy accumulated within curved beads that sparked multiple conflicts has clad itself in fire and become a Pokémon.
name: Chi-Yu

description: According to an article in a dubious magazine, this Pokémon has some connection to a phenomenon that occurs in a certain region.
name: Roaring Moon

description: It’s possible that this is the object listed as Iron Valiant in a certain expedition journal.
name: Iron Valiant

description: This Pokémon resembles Cyclizar, but it is far burlier and more ferocious. Nothing is known about its ecology or other features.
name: Koraidon

description: This seems to be the Iron Serpent mentioned in an old book. The Iron Serpent is said to have turned the land to ash with its lightning.
name: Miraidon

description: It resembles an illustration published in a paranormal magazine, said to be a depiction of a super-ancient Suicune.
name: Walking Wake

description: According to the few eyewitness accounts that exist, it used its shining blades to julienne large trees and boulders.
name: Iron Leaves

description: The head and tail appear to belong to two separate creatures; both help each other out from within their shared apple. Dipplin coat their apples with syrup produced within their bodies. The layers of fragrant syrup beguile opponents.​
name: Dipplin

description: Poltchageist has a swirl pattern not unlike Sinistea's - but unlike Sinistea, its swirl is not a weakness. After a target is sprinkled with some of Poltchageist's powdery body or eats food dusted with it, Poltchageist drains their life-force and absorbs it as energy.​
name: Poltchageist

description: It prefers cool, dark places, such as the back of a shelf or the space beneath a home's floorboards. It wanders in search of prey after sunset.
name: Sinistcha

description: Okidogi is a ruffian with a short temper. It can pulverize anything by swinging around the chain on its neck.
name: Okidogi

description: Munkidori keeps itself somewhere safe while it toys with its foes, using psychokinesis to induce intense dizziness.
name: Munkidori

description: Fezandipiti beats its glossy wings to scatter pheromones that captivate people and Pokémon.
name: Fezandipiti

description: This mischief-loving Pokémon is full of curiosity. It battles by drawing out the type-based energy contained within its masks.
name: Ogerpon

description: It digs holes on mountains, searching for food. It’s so durable that being caught in a cave-in won’t faze it.
name: Archaludon

description: These capricious syrpents have banded together. On the rare occasion that their moods align, their true power is unleashed.
name: Hydrapple

description: It resembles an eerie Pokémon once shown in a paranormal magazine. That Pokémon was said to be an Entei regenerated from a fossil.
name: Gouging Fire

description: It bears resemblance to a Pokémon that became a hot topic for a short while after a paranormal magazine touted it as Raikou's ancestor.
name: Raging Bolt

description: It was named after a mysterious object recorded in an old book. Its body seems to be metallic.
name: Iron Boulder

description: There was supposedly an incident in which it launched shining blades to cut everything around it to pieces. Little else is known about it.
name: Iron Crown

description: It’s thought that this Pokémon lived in ancient Paldea until it got caught in seismic shifts and went extinct.
name: Terapagos

description: Its peach-shaped shell serves as storage for a potent poison. It makes poisonous mochi and serves them to people and Pokémon.
name: Pecharunt
Defense Deoxys
names: ディフェンスフォルム

description: Its earthen skin is reasonably hard—it has no problem repelling a Starly’s pecking, at least.
name: Sandy Wormadam

description: Its body, composed of refuse, blends in to the scenery so much as to be inconspicuous. This seems to be the perfect way for the Pokémon to evade the detection of predators.
name: Trash Wormadam

description: Upon taking in the scent of a particular rare flower, Shaymin is enveloped in light, and its tiny body transforms. I took a whiff of the flower myself, but alas, my body remained unchanged.
name: Sky Shaymin

description: Giratina loses its legs upon changing into this form. I believe this Pokémon must hail from a world where the heavens and the earth are as one, though I have no way of proving it.
name: Origin Giratina

description: This Rotom has possessed a convection microwave oven. It will sear the surrounding area with its burning heat, then smile in delight.
name: Heat Rotom

description: The model of washing machine that Rotom can inspirit has been discontinued, so these appliances are now traded at high prices.
name: Wash Rotom

description: The special motor within the refrigerator is the key to bringing about Rotom’s change in form.
name: Frost Rotom

description: There are several appliances that Rotom can inspirit, but the first one to be developed was the electric fan.
name: Fan Rotom

description: This Rotom has possessed a lawn mower. It will mow down grass and flowers, then swagger around with pride at its accomplishments.
name: Mow Rotom

description: Castform changes to this form when it basks in bright sunlight. When you touch its glowing skin, it feels all dried out!
name: Sunny Castform

description: This is Castform’s form when pelted by rain. In an experiment where it was placed in a shower, this Pokémon didn’t change to this form.
name: Rainy Castform

description: This is Castform’s form when caught in a hailstorm. Its whole body is chilled, and its skin is partially frozen!
name: Snowy Castform

description: The power of its jaws is immense—enough to leave teeth marks in iron sheets. Its personality is also extremely vicious.
name: Blue-Striped Basculin

description: When wounded, it stops moving. It goes as still as stone to meditate, sharpening its mind and spirit.
name: Zen Darmanitan

description: An example of what is known as a “form change,” though I suspect this strange avian guise to be Tornadus’s true form. Tornadus has been sighted crossing the ocean while in this form.
name: Therian Tornadus

description: Quick as a flash, it materializes out of nowhere. It pulverizes foes into nothingness with showers of devastatingly powerful lightning bolts launched from the string of orbs on its tail.
name: Therian Thundurus

description: Landorus soars through the sky in this form, bestowing plentiful harvests upon the land and earning the people’s reverence. It can traverse the whole of Hisui in a mere couple of hours.
name: Therian Landorus

description: The sameness of Zekrom’s and Kyurem’s genes allowed Kyurem to absorb Zekrom. Kyurem can now use the power of both electricity and ice.
name: Black Kyurem

description: It has foreseen that a world of truth will arrive for people and Pokémon. It strives to protect that future.
name: White Kyurem

description: The power that lay hidden in its body now covers its horn, turning it into a sword that can slice through anything.
name: Resolute Keldeo

description: Once upon a time, a king with an Aegislash reigned over the land. His Pokémon eventually drained him of life, and his kingdom fell with him.
name: Blade Aegislash

description: Small Pumpkaboo are said to be the product of areas where few lost souls lingered.
name: Small Pumpkaboo

description: Large Pumpkaboo are said to be the product of areas where many lost souls lingered.
name: Large Pumpkaboo

description: Massive Pumpkaboo are said to be the product of areas where a great number of lost souls lingered.
name: Super Pumpkaboo

description: A small-sized Pumpkaboo evolves into a small-sized Gourgeist. Its bodily proportions also get passed on to its descendants.
name: Small Gourgeist

description: A large-sized Pumpkaboo evolves into a large-sized Gourgeist. Its bodily proportions also get passed on to its descendants.
name: Large Gourgeist

description: A supersized Pumpkaboo evolves into a supersized Gourgeist. Its bodily proportions also get passed on to its descendants.
name: Super Gourgeist

description: In order to support its flower, which has grown larger due to Mega Evolution, its back and legs have become stronger.
name: Mega Venusaur

description: The overwhelming power that fills its entire body causes it to turn black and create intense blue flames.
name: Mega Charizard X

description: Its bond with its Trainer is the source of its power. It boasts speed and maneuverability greater than that of a jet fighter.
name: Mega Charizard Y

description: The cannon on its back is as powerful as a tank gun. Its tough legs and back enable it to withstand the recoil from firing the cannon.
name: Mega Blastoise

description: It’s adept at precognition. When attacks completely miss Alakazam, that’s because it’s seeing the future.
name: Mega Alakazam

description: It can pass through other dimensions and can appear anywhere. It caused a stir one time when it stuck just one leg out of a wall.
name: Mega Gengar

description: Its child has grown rapidly, thanks to the energy of Mega Evolution. Mother and child show their harmonious teamwork in battle.
name: Mega Kangaskhan

description: With its vaunted horns, it can lift an opponent 10 times heavier than itself and fly about with ease.
name: Mega Pinsir

description: Although it obeys its instinctive drive to destroy everything within its reach, it will respond to orders from a Trainer it truly trusts.
name: Mega Gyarados

description: The power of Mega Evolution has completely restored its genes. The rocks on its body are harder than diamond.
name: Mega Aerodactyl

description: Psychic power has augmented its muscles. It has a grip strength of one ton and can sprint a hundred meters in two seconds flat!
name: Mega Mewtwo X

description: Despite its diminished size, its mental power has grown phenomenally. With a mere thought, it can smash a skyscraper to smithereens.
name: Mega Mewtwo Y

description: Massive amounts of energy intensely stimulated Ampharos’s cells, apparently awakening its long-sleeping dragon’s blood.
name: Mega Ampharos

description: It’s better at beating things than grasping them. When it battles for a long time, the weight of its pincers becomes too much to bear.
name: Mega Scizor

description: A tremendous influx of energy builds it up, but when Mega Evolution ends, Heracross is bothered by terrible soreness in its muscles.
name: Mega Heracross

description: Houndoom’s entire body generates heat when it Mega Evolves. Its fearsome fiery breath turns its opponents to ash.
name: Mega Houndoom

description: The effects of Mega Evolution make it more ferocious than ever. It’s unclear whether it can even hear its Trainer’s orders.

description: Its two sets of jaws thrash about violently as if they each had a will of their own. One gnash from them can turn a boulder to dust.
