description: Too much electricity has built up in its body, irritating Manectric. Its explosive speed is equal to that of a lightning bolt.

description: Mega Evolution increases its vindictiveness, and the cursing power that was held back by its zipper comes spilling out.

description: It converts the energy from Mega Evolution into an intimidating aura. Fainthearted people expire from shock at the sight of it.

description: Its disposition is more vicious than before its Mega Evolution. Garchomp carves its opponents up with the scythes on both arms.

description: Bathed in explosive energy, its combative instincts have awakened. For its enemies, it has no mercy whatsoever.

description: It blocks any and all attacks with its giant-sized gemstone. However, the stone’s a heavy burden, and it limits Mega Sableye’s movements.

description: The moment it charges into its opponent, sharp spikes pop out of Sharpedo’s head, leaving its opponent with deep wounds.

description: Under the influence of Shellder’s digestive fluids, Slowpoke has awakened, gaining a great deal of power—and a little motivation to boot.
name: Mega Slowbro

description: With its muscular strength now greatly increased, it can fly continuously for two weeks without resting.

description: The power of Mega Evolution was so strong that it smashed Glalie’s jaw. Its inability to eat very well leaves Glalie irritated.

description: When it knows it can’t win, it digs the claws on its legs into its opponent and starts the countdown to a big explosion.

description: Its three hairs change shape depending on Diglett’s mood. They’re a useful communication tool among these Pokémon.
name: Alolan Diglett

description: The three of them get along very well. Through their formidable teamwork, they defeat powerful opponents.

description: Deeply proud and keenly smart, this Pokémon moves with cunning during battle and relentlessly attacks enemies’ weak points.

description: This Pokémon is one tough opponent. Not only does it have formidable physical abilities, but it’s also not above fighting dirty.

description: When it comes rolling down a mountain path, anything in its way gets zapped by electricity and sent flying.

description: It uses magnetism to accelerate and fire off rocks tinged with electricity. Even if it doesn’t score a direct hit, the jolt of electricity will do the job.
name: Alolan Golem

description: It has a passion for trash above all else, speedily digesting it and creating brilliant crystals of sparkling poison.
name: Alolan Grimer

description: Muk’s coloration becomes increasingly vivid the more it feasts on its favorite dish—trash.

description: This Pokémon’s psychic powers aren’t as strong as they once were. The head on this Exeggutor’s tail scans surrounding areas with weak telepathy.
name: Alolan Exeggutor

description: The cursed flames that light up the bone carried by this Pokémon are said to cause both mental and physical pain that will never fade.
name: Alolan Marowak

name: Busted Mimikyu

description: It functions thanks to its artificial soul. The vivid decoration is proof that it was presented as a gift to royalty.
name: Original Magearna

name: Partner Cap Pikachu

description: These Pokémon have both calm and ferocious qualities. It’s said that this form of Lycanroc is the most troublesome to raise.
name: Dusk Lycanroc

description: Necrozma has attached itself to Solgaleo. It siphons away its host’s limitless energy, exploiting that energy to fuel a rampage.
name: Dusk Mane Necrozma

description: When Necrozma latches on to Lunala, it becomes vicious, seeing enemies everywhere it looks. It will burn the world with lasers.
name: Dawn Wings Necrozma

description: The light pouring out from all over its body affects living things and nature, impacting them in various ways.
name: Ultra Necrozma

description: These daring Pokémon have coins on their foreheads. Darker coins are harder, and harder coins garner more respect among Meowth.
name: Galarian Meowth

description: This Pokémon will look into your eyes and read the contents of your heart. If it finds evil there, it promptly hides away.
name: Galarian Ponyta

description: Brave and prideful, this Pokémon dashes airily through the forest, its steps aided by the psychic power stored in the fur on its fetlocks.
name: Galarian Rapidash

description: Because Galarian Slowpoke eat the seeds of a plant that grows only in Galar, their tails have developed a spicy flavor.
name: Galarian Slowpoke

description: If this Pokémon squeezes the tongue of the Shellder biting it, the Shellder will launch a toxic liquid from the tip of its shell.
name: Galarian Slowbro

description: The stalks of leeks are thicker and longer in the Galar region. Farfetch’d that adapted to these stalks took on a unique form.
name: Galarian Farfetch'd

description: Long ago, during a time when droves of factories fouled the air with pollution, Weezing changed into this form for some reason.
name: Galarian Weezing

description: It can radiate chilliness from the bottoms of its feet. It’ll spend the whole day tap-dancing on a frozen floor.
name: Galarian Mr. Mime

description: Known as Articuno, this Pokémon fires beams that can immobilize opponents as if they had been frozen solid.
name: Galarian Articuno

description: One kick from its powerful legs will pulverize a dump truck. Supposedly, this Pokémon runs through the mountains at over 180 mph.
name: Galarian Zapdos

description: The sinister aura that blazes like molten fire around this Pokémon is what inspired the name Moltres.
name: Galarian Moltres

description: While chanting strange spells, this Pokémon combines its internal toxins with what it’s eaten, creating strange potions.
name: Galarian Slowking

description: Sudden climate change wiped out this ancient kind of Corsola. This Pokémon absorbs others’ life-force through its branches.
name: Galarian Corsola

description: Thought to be the oldest form of Zigzagoon, it moves in zigzags and wreaks havoc upon its surroundings.
name: Galarian Zigzagoon

description: This very aggressive Pokémon will recklessly challenge opponents stronger than itself.
name: Galarian Linoone

description: The colder they get, the more energetic they are. They freeze their breath to make snowballs, using them as ammo for playful snowball fights.
name: Galarian Darumaka

description: Though it has a gentle disposition, it’s also very strong. It will quickly freeze the snowball on its head before going for a headbutt.
name: Galarian Darmanitan

description: Darmanitan takes this form when enraged. It won’t stop spewing flames until its rage has settled, even if its body starts to melt.
name: Galarian Zen Darmanitan

description: It’s said that this Pokémon was formed when an ancient clay tablet was drawn to a vengeful spirit.
name: Galarian Yamask

description: Its conspicuous lips lure prey in as it lies in wait in the mud. When prey gets close, Stunfisk clamps its jagged steel fins down on them.
name: Galarian Stunfisk

description: As it gulps down stagnant water and generates electricity in its body, a sound like a rhythm played by a bass guitar reverberates all around.
name: Low Key Toxtricity

description: If you lick the ice covering its face, you’ll find it has a faintly salty taste. This species rode here on ocean currents from a cold, faraway land.
name: Noice Face Eiscue

description: Able to cut down anything with a single strike, it became known as the Fairy King’s Sword, and it inspired awe in friend and foe alike.
name: Crowned Zacian

description: Now that it’s equipped with its shield, it can shrug off impressive blows, including the attacks of Dynamax Pokémon.
name: Crowned Zamazenta

description: This form of Urshifu is a strong believer in defeating foes by raining many blows down on them. Its strikes are nonstop, flowing like a river.
name: Rapid Strike Urshifu

description: It’s said that this Pokémon once moved a large forest—and all the Pokémon living there—to a new location overnight.
name: Ice Rider Calyrex

description: Legend says that by using its power to see all events from past to future, this Pokémon saved the creatures of a forest from a meteorite strike.
name: Shadow Rider Calyrex

description: Huge amounts of pollen burst from it with the force of a volcanic eruption. Breathing in too much of the pollen can cause fainting.
name: Gigantamax Venusaur

description: The flame inside its body burns hotter than 3,600 degrees Fahrenheit. When Charizard roars, that temperature climbs even higher.
name: Gigantamax Charizard

description: Water fired from this Pokémon's central main cannon has enough power to blast a hole into a mountain.
name: Gigantamax Blastoise

description: Once it has opponents trapped in a tornado that could blow away a 10-ton truck, it finishes them off with its poisonous scales.
name: Gigantamax Butterfree

description: When it smashes its opponents with its bolt- shaped tail, it delivers a surge of electricity equivalent to a lightning strike.
name: Gigantamax Pikachu

description: Its body has grown incredibly long and the coin on its forehead has grown incredibly large—all thanks to Gigantamax power.
name: Gigantamax Meowth

description: One of these Pokémon once used its immeasurable strength to lift a large ship that was in trouble. It then carried the ship to port.
name: Gigantamax Machamp

description: It lays traps, hoping to steal the lives of those it catches. If you stand in front of its mouth, you’ll hear your loved ones’ voices calling out to you.
name: Gigantamax Gengar

description: The bubbles it spews out are strongly alkaline. Any opponents hit by them will have their bodies quickly melted away.
name: Gigantamax Kingler

description: It surrounds itself with a huge ring of gathered ice particles. It uses the ring to smash any icebergs that might impede its graceful swimming.
name: Gigantamax Lapras

description: Having gotten even friendlier and more innocent, Eevee tries to play with anyone around, only to end up crushing them with its immense body.
name: Gigantamax Eevee

description: Terrifyingly strong, this Pokémon is the size of a mountain—and moves about as much as one as well.
name: Gigantamax Snorlax

description: It sprays toxic gas from its mouth and fingers. If the gas engulfs you, the toxins will seep in all the way down to your bones.
name: Gigantamax Garbodor

description: It can send electric beams streaking out from the hole in its belly. The beams’ tremendous energy can vaporize an opponent in one shot.
name: Gigantamax Melmetal

description: Rillaboom has become one with its forest of drums and continues to lay down beats that shake all of Galar.
name: Gigantamax Rillaboom

description: Gigantamax energy can sometimes cause the diameter of this Pokémon’s fireball to exceed 300 feet.
name: Gigantamax Cinderace

description: It has excellent sniping skills. Shooting a berry rolling along over nine miles away is a piece of cake for this Pokémon.
name: Gigantamax Inteleon

description: The eight feathers on its back are called blade birds, and they can launch off its body to attack foes independently.
name: Gigantamax Corviknight

description: If it were to utilize every last bit of its power, it could control the minds of every living being in its vicinity.
name: Gigantamax Orbeetle

description: In the Galar region, there’s a tale about this Pokémon chewing up a mountain and using the rubble to stop a flood.
name: Gigantamax Drednaw

description: When Galar was hit by a harsh cold wave, this Pokémon served as a giant heating stove and saved many lives.
name: Gigantamax Coalossal

description: If it stretches its neck, the strong aroma of its nectar pours out. The scent is so sickeningly sweet that one whiff makes other Pokémon faint.
name: Gigantamax Flapple

description: Due to Gigantamax energy, this Pokémon’s nectar has thickened. The increased viscosity lets the nectar absorb more damage than before.
name: Gigantamax Appletun

description: Sand swirls around its body with such speed and power that it could pulverize a skyscraper.
name: Gigantamax Sandaconda

description: Out of control after its own poison penetrated its brain, it tears across the land in a rampage, contaminating the earth with toxic sweat.
name: Gigantamax Amped Toxtricity

description: The heat that comes off a Gigantamax Centiskorch may destabilize air currents. Sometimes it can even cause storms.
name: Gigantamax Centiskorch

description: Beams like lightning shoot down from its tentacles. It’s known to some as the Raging Goddess.
name: Gigantamax Hatterene

description: Gigantamax energy has caused more hair to sprout all over its body. With the added strength, it can jump over the world’s tallest building.
name: Gigantamax Grimmsnarl

description: It launches swarms of missiles, each made of cream and loaded with 100,000 kilocalories. Get hit by one of these, and your head will swim.
name: Gigantamax Alcremie

description: After this Pokémon has Gigantamaxed, its massive nose can utterly demolish large structures with a single smashing blow.
name: Gigantamax Copperajah

description: The hardness of its cells is exceptional, even among Steel types. It also has a body structure that’s resistant to earthquakes.
name: Gigantamax Duraludon

description: Infinite amounts of energy pour from this Pokémon’s enlarged core, warping the surrounding space-time.
name: Eternamax Eternatus

description: The energy released by this Pokémon’s fists forms shock waves that can blow away Dynamax Pokémon in just one hit.
name: Gigantamax Single Strike Urshifu

description: All it takes is a glare from this Pokémon to take the lives of those with evil in their hearts—or so they say.
name: Gigantamax Rapid Strike Urshifu

description: Out of control after its own poison penetrated its brain, it tears across the land in a rampage, contaminating the earth with toxic sweat.
name: Gigantamax Low Key Toxtricity

description: They patrol their territory in pairs. I believe the igneous rock components in the fur of this species are the result of volcanic activity in its habitat.
name: Hisuian Growlithe

description: Snaps at its foes with fangs cloaked in blazing flame. Despite its bulk, it deftly feints every which way, leading opponents on a deceptively merry chase as it all but dances around them.
name: Hisuian Arcanine

description: An enigmatic Pokémon that happens to bear a resemblance to a Poké Ball. When excited, it discharges the electric current it has stored in its belly, then lets out a great, uproarious laugh.
name: Hisuian Voltorb

description: The tissue on the surface of its body is curiously similar in composition to an Apricorn. When irritated, this Pokémon lets loose an electric current equal to 20 lightning bolts.
name: Hisuian Electrode

description: Said to purify lost, forsaken souls with its flames and guide them to the afterlife. I believe its form has been influenced by the energy of the sacred mountain towering at Hisui’s center.
name: Hisuian Typhlosion

description: Fishers detest this troublesome Pokémon because it sprays poison from its spines, getting it everywhere. A different form of Qwilfish lives in other regions.
name: Hisuian Qwilfish

description: Its sturdy, curved claws are ideal for traversing precipitous cliffs. From the tips of these claws drips a venom that infiltrates the nerves of any prey caught in Sneasel’s grasp.
name: Hisuian Sneasel

description: Hard of heart and deft of blade, this rare form of Samurott is a product of the Pokémon’s evolution in the region of Hisui. Its turbulent blows crash into foes like ceaseless pounding waves.
name: Hisuian Samurott

description: I suspect that its well-developed legs are the result of a life spent on mountains covered in deep snow. The scent it exudes from its flower crown heartens those in proximity.
name: Hisuian Lilligant

description: A once-departed soul, returned to life in Hisui. Derives power from resentment, which rises as energy atop its head and takes on the forms of foes. In this way, Zorua vents lingering malice.
name: Hisuian Zorua

description: With its disheveled white fur, it looks like an embodiment of death. Heedless of its own safety, Zoroark attacks its nemeses with a bitter energy so intense, it lacerates Zoroark’s own body.
name: Hisuian Zoroark

description: Screaming a bloodcurdling battle cry, this huge and ferocious bird Pokémon goes out on the hunt. It blasts lakes with shock waves, then scoops up any prey that float to the water’s surface.
name: Hisuian Braviary

description: A creature given to melancholy. I suspect its metallic shell developed as a result of the mucus on its skin reacting with the iron in Hisui’s water.
name: Hisuian Sliggoo

description: Able to freely control the hardness of its metallic shell. It loathes solitude and is extremely clingy—it will fume and run riot if those dearest to it ever leave its side.
name: Hisuian Goodra

description: The armor of ice covering its lower jaw puts steel to shame and can shatter rocks with ease. This Pokémon barrels along steep mountain paths, cleaving through the deep snow.
name: Hisuian Avalugg

description: The air stored inside the rachises of Decidueye’s feathers insulates the Pokémon against Hisui’s extreme cold. This is firm proof that evolution can be influenced by environment.
name: Hisuian Decidueye

description: It soars across the sky in a form that greatly resembles the creator of all things. Perhaps this imitation of appearance is Palkia’s strategy for gaining Arceus’s powers.
name: Origin Palkia

description: Radiant light caused Dialga to take on a form bearing a striking resemblance to the creator Pokémon. Dialga now wields such colossal strength that one must conclude this is its true form.
name: Origin Dialga

description: This Pikachu wears its partner’s cap—proof of the strong bond Pikachu and its partner formed as the two overcame many hardships together.
name: Partner Pikachu

description: It can evolve into a variety of forms. Eevee's genes are the key to solving the mysteries of Pokémon evolution.
name: Partner Eevee

description: The slightest shock is sometimes enough to get this Pokémon to spit out the Arrokuda lodged in its throat.
name: Gulping Cramorant

description: The half-swallowed Pikachu is so startled that it isn’t struggling yet, but it’s still looking for a chance to strike back.
name: Gorging Cramorant

description: Hunger hormones affect its temperament. Until its hunger is appeased, it gets up to all manner of evil deeds.
name: Hangry Morpeko

description: This Zarude’s special strength stems from its love and care for an orphaned human child that the Pokémon has raised since the child’s infancy.
name: Dada Zarude

description: Though it differs from other Basculin in several respects, including demeanor—this one is gentle—I have categorized it as a regional form given the vast array of shared qualities.
name: White-Striped Basculin

description: A different guise from its feminine humanoid form. From the clouds, it descends upon those who treat any form of life with disrespect and metes out wrathful, ruthless punishment.
name: Therian Enamorus

description: This kind of Tauros, known as the Combat Breed, is distinguished by its thick, powerful muscles and its fierce disposition.
name: Combat Breed Tauros

description: People call this kind of Tauros the Blaze Breed due to the hot air it snorts from its nostrils. Its three tails are intertwined.
name: Blaze Breed Tauros

description: It swims by jetting water from its horns. The most notable characteristic of the Aqua Breed is its high body fat, which allows it to float easily.
name: Aqua Breed Tauros

description: It’s dangerous for Wooper to travel alone. They line up in groups of three or four and help each other as they walk around the wetlands.
name: Paldean Wooper

description: A recent study uncovered that the number of segments a Dudunsparce’s body has is determined by the Pokémon’s genes.
name: Three-Segment Dudunsparce

description: This hero of the ocean swims at a speed of 50 knots and saves drowning people and Pokémon.
name: Hero Palafin

description: The little one just appeared one day. They all live together like a family, but the relationship between the three is still unclear.
name: Family of Three Maushold

description: This Pokémon tricks its opponents by playing dead. It is small and weak, but it uses its smarts to survive.
name: Droopy Tatsugiri

description: It’s one of the most intelligent dragon Pokémon. It camouflages itself by inflating its throat sac.
name: Stretchy Tatsugiri

description: Blue-feathered Squawkabilly view their green-feathered counterparts as rivals, since the latter make up the largest, most powerful groups.
name: Blue Plumage Squawkabilly

description: The yellow Squawkabilly are especially fierce. They’ve even been known to drive other bird Pokémon out of town.
name: Yellow Plumage Squawkabilly

description: Though these Squawkabilly are the fewest in number, they have no trouble living in towns since they blend in with the white buildings.
name: White Plumage Squawkabilly

description: It wanders around, carrying an old coin on its back. It survives by draining the life-force from humans who try to pick up its coin.
name: Roaming Gimmighoul

description: This special Ursaluna can see in the dark with its left eye and protects itself with mud that is as hard as iron.
name: Bloodmoon Ursaluna

description: In this form, it draws on the power of water. It attacks unrelentingly with kicks and ivy strikes.
name: Wellspring Mask Ogerpon

description: In this form, it draws on the power of fire. It spears its enemies with thorn-covered ivy.
name: Hearthflame Mask Ogerpon

description: In this form, it draws on the power of stone. Its body is rock-solid, protecting it from all manner of attacks.

description: This Pokémon converts snowflakes into baubles, which it stores in pine trees. It can easily go a whole week dancing around Christmas trees out of joy.
name: Christmas Tree Smoliv

description: It basks in the light of the stars to its heart’s content until the star on its head shines bright. After that, Christmas Tree Dolliv places the star on top of a decorated pine tree and goes on a journey for a new star.
name: Christmas Tree Dolliv

description: This Pokémon gathers friends by launching its rich, shiny lights at them and pulling them closer to itself.
name: Christmas Tree Arboliva

description: Its cloak looks to be made of soft, fluffy snow, but don't be deceived. This packed, hardened snow offers it sturdy protection and gives frostbite to any who touch it.
name: Snowmadam

description: Males swing their head plumage to attract females. The females' flying abilities are shown to impress the male.
name: Lovebird Unfezant

description: The defensive instinct of the males is strong. It's when they're protecting their partners that they unleash their full power.
name: Snoozing Meowstic

description: The way it protects itself by flailing its arms may be an adorable sight, but stay well away. This is flailing that can snap thick tree trunks.
name: Polar Stufful

description: This catlike subspecies of Sneasler has further adapted to its frozen climate, becoming an even more elusive, deadly predator.
name: Snow Leopard Sneasler

description: Attached to its head is a huge set of several jaws formed by horns. These can chew through iron beams.
name: Overgrown Mawile

description: It blooms during times of strong sunlight. It tries to make up for everything it endured as a bud. The more blossom it has, the darker their past.
name: Blossom Cherrim

description: It binds itself to trees in marshes. It attracts prey with its sweet-smelling flowers and gulps them down.
name: Overgrown Carnivine

description: Adores circular objects. Wanders the forests to look for dropped eggs to paint.
name: Egg Painter Meowth

description: It distracts by flinging around its tail in the bushes, showing as if it’s an Easter egg. When close enough, it jumps out of the bushes to surprise you.
name: Easter Egg Azurill

description: Swanna start to gather flowers at dawn. It makes flower crowns for the new duckletts.
name: Flower Family Swanna

description: When it's surprised or excited, the 14 fur spikes on its back will stand up and light up in different colours.
name: Easter Togedemaru

description: It searches for food all day. It possesses a keen sense of smell but doesn’t use it for anything other than foraging chocolate eggs.
name: Egg Forager Lechonk

description: It looks like a birthday cake come to life. If you approach it because it's cute, it could give you a slice of cake as a reward.
name: Birthday Cake Alopix

description: It is cloaked entirely in al dente pasta and meatballs, preventing any glimpse of its true identity. The pasta, meatballs and various spices make for a hearty meal.
name: Pasta Bolognese Tangela

description: It has a small heart and brain. Its stomach comprises most of its body along with beansprouts and other fillings, all wrapped in nori.
name: Temaki Gulpin

description: During the summer when the weather warms, Ice Cream Spheals prefer living in groups on the cone to keep each other cool.
name: Ice Cream Spheals

description: It makes a single peach flavored pearl during its lifetime. The pearl along with the crumbly shell is said to amplify the fruity flavor.
name: Clamacaron

description: The two cutlery employ a strategy of rapidly alternating between fork and knife to spear and slice food elegantly.
name: Fancy Cutlery Doublade

description: It's covered in a caramel membrane that makes any person desire a bite.
name: Goomy Brûlée

description: It lives inside a slice of strawberry shortcake. When a Strawberry Shortcake Applin is separated from its slice, its body loses sugar and the Pokémon grows weak.
name: Strawberry Shortcake Applin

description: The leader dango, distinguished by the number of strawberries, uses the skewer to signal the others when it's time to rearrange.
name: Dango Falinks

description: When this Pokémon expands and contracts its rice-y body, the seaweed on its stomach keeps the rice from popping out.
name: Onigiri Bellibolt

description: When it gets dark, the rainbow light from its bright, shiny horns form a rainbow in the sky.
name: Pride Ampharos

description: Although its outer shell is uncommonly durable, the shock of falling to the ground smashes the shell to smithereens, revealing its mesmerizing colourful patterns underneath.
name: Rainbow Minior

description: It eats all kinds of coloured berries nonstop—a habit that has made it more resilient than it looks. It'll show up on farms, searching for the brightest coloured berries.
name: Painted Acorn Skwovet

description: It controls the colours of flames burning at over 3,000 degrees Celsius. It casually swims through the sea of lava it creates by melting rock and sand.
name: Gradient Chi-Yu

description: Known as the legendary bird of fire. Moltres is the perfect Pokémon to carry the Olympic Flame into the stadium.
name: Olympic Flame Moltres

description: They take turns helping with archery when the team is finished. They sometimes run in too fast and jump behind a target for protection.
name: Archery Sentret

description: These bird Pokémon are excellent at waterpolo. They swim around in the water throwing balls and plants at each other to train.
name: Waterpolo Ducklett

description: While it prides itself on its varied kicking moves, it can also run really fast once its flames have heated up its feet.
name: Relay Race Raboot

description: It uses special lenses in its eyes to sense things about its opponents—like their body heat—then poke once it identifies a weak spot.
name: Fencinteleon

description: It stores poison in an internal poison sac and secretes that poison through its skin. You better not touch its skin during the fight!
name: Boxel

description: It lifts the team spirit with its cheerful dance moves. They are so good at dancing, that even the opponents gets a spirit boost.
name: Cheerleader Oricorio

description: The fin on Mudkip's head acts as highly sensitive radar. Using this fin to sense magic in the air, this Pokémon can determine what is taking place around it without using its eyes.
name: Moon Fairy Mudkip

description: When it finds a flower it likes, it dwells on that flower its whole life long and even sleeps on the flower to draw energy to heal.
name: Flower Fairy Flabébé

description: Its venom sacs produce a fluid that this Pokémon then heats up with the flame in its tail. This process creates Salandit's fire wings.
name: Fire Fairy Salandit

description: A common sight in cities and villages. It flies between homes to hang Papel Picado.
name: Papel Picado Pidgey

description: Its sombrero is its pride, which it shows off during Día de Muertos.
name: Sombrero Lotad

description: Duskull can pass through any wall no matter how thick it may be. Once this Pokémon chooses a target, it will dance around them until the break of dawn.
name: Sugar Duskull

description: These Pokémon arose from the spirits of people interred in graves. They search for their families on Día de Muertos, connecting with loved ones and sharing memories of its former life.
name: Honoring Yamask

description: Instead of gazing at the stars for the future, Monarch Gothitelle gazes into the past, through the souls of the departed, in order to share favored memories with their loved ones on Día de Muertos.
name: Monarch Gothitelle

description: Its vibrant, colorful fur shines brightly as it flies through the sky, guiding spirits to their loved ones on Día de Muertos.
name: Alebrije Pyroar

description: The fragrance of its flower differs slightly on Día de Muertos, its scent becomes sweeter. Sniffing the aroma calms your heart and mind.
name: La Catrina Hisuian Lilligant

description: Before it gets cold in wintertime, its habit is to hoard warm sweaters and blankets to make its home cosy.
name: Sweater Teddiursa

description: It moves by spinning on its foot. It makes little leafy whirlwinds with its movement.
name: Leafy Baltoy

description: This Pokémon lives for the thrill of colder times. It drinks hot choco while watching the leaves fall.
name: Cosy Perrserker

description: This glutton appears in houses without warning and devours the entirety of their milk and cookies—such occurrences have long been counted among the merriest of surprises.
name: Santa Snorlax

description: When the jolly snowfall season starts, cranking the spring draws it out to dance in the open.
name: Music Box Bellossom

description: Once the hot seasons end, its coat will be replaced with soft wooly fur that holds a lot of insulating air in preparation for the colder weather.
name: Doll Lopunny

description: It lowers its body heat to freeze its fur. The hairs then become like needles it can fire.
name: Snowglobe Glaceon

description: This Pokémon has a kind heart. By touching with its feelers, Elf Audino can find out other creatures’ wishes and desires.
name: Elf Audino

description: It lives deep within the forest. Even after evolving into this splendid form, it hasn’t given up on its mischievous antics and holiday pranks.
name: Grinchsnarl

description: Though they look like candy canes, Candy Cane Wiglett is a living pokémon. The resemblance seems to be a coincidental result of festive adaptation.
name: Candy Cane Wiglett

description: It lives inside a gingerbread house. Sometimes it gets left in gift shop corners during the holidays since no one realizes it’s actually a Pokémon.
name: Gingerbread Gimmighoul

description: With its tail, Serperior holds a lantern to celebrate Lunar New Year. Its wooden body radiates charm and grace.
name: Wooden Serperior

description: This Pokémon appears on Lunar New Year, just before the celebration starts, so kids wait for its arrival.
name: Paper Lantern Lampent

description: This hot-blooded Pokémon is filled with energy. When it gets excited or starts dancing, its body gets hot.
name: Lion Dancer Litleo

description: These bird Pokémon are excellent divers. They can swim from day one and start diving after the first week.
name: Baby Ducklett

description: When Pancham are born, they don’t start glaring immediately—they only begin to glare once they swap their pacifier for a leaf to chew on.
name: Pacifier Pancham

description: These key collectors love to play around with toy keys when they live in a household with babies.
name: Baby Toy Klefki

description: This Pokémon is sweet, and smooth to the touch. Fragrance in Fidough’s breath attracts customers into the bakery.
name: Hearts Fidough

description: Bombirdier uses the apron on its chest to bundle up baby Pokémon, which it carries to their parents.
name: Love Bombirdier

description: The aroma that rises from the flowers contains a substance that makes anyone happy.
name: Shamrock Meganium

description: The shell on its back carries a cauldron. On a very happy Turtwig, the cauldron is full of gold.
name: Treasure Turtwig

description: During St Patrick's Day, Sinistea will "drown the shamrock" in its tea before throwing it over the shoulder for good luck.
name: Good Luck Sinistea

description: An attempt to fix its faulty programming failed, corrupting it further and resulting in this glitched form.
name: Porygon-X

description: In a world dominated by AI, a powerful Darkrai is trapped in a decaying virtual Pokémon battle system. Twisted by data corruption, it moves between reality and broken digital realms, dragging victims into a fractured dreamscape.
name: Error Darkrai

description: In an alternate universe, Glitched Beta Arceus emerged from equations which it bends to shape the world in bits and bytes.
name: Glitched Beta Arceus

description: Eevee’s unstable genes have led to a genetic malfunction during evolution, resulting in Sylvirus’ misshapen and jagged appearance.
name: Sylvirus

description: An error caused by corrupted ultra wormholes makes its explosions stronger than any before it.
name: Corrupted Blacephalon

description: A gentle soul that can read the minds of others. It can ferry eggs across the sea on its back.
name: Egg Nest Lapras

description: It can transform into anything. It likes to fool people during Easter by transforming into an Easter egg.
name: Cracked Ditto

description: It lives in groups by the water. During Easter, it plays the role of Easter Bunny for nearby villages to entertain the children.
name: Easter Bidoof

description: Appears in filthy dungeons. Thrives by sucking up metals like swords and armor from adventurers.
name: Cube Slime Grimer

description: It is said that this Pokémon lives somewhere deep in the mountains and that it flies. However, it is only a rumor.
name: Guardian Dragonite

description: Strong feelings of grief turned a soul into a Pokémon. If it opens its mouth, its cursed energy escapes.
name: Banshee Banette

description: By allowing its cry to resonate in the hollow of its belly, it produces magic.
name: Wizard Kricketune

description: It is a common sight around cave entrances. It is known to rescue people and keep evil at bay.
name: Ranger Floatzel

description: Its knuckle claws secrete a toxin that is used for battles in dungeons.
name: Rogue Toxicroak

description: Its cute music act is a ruse. When victims let down their guard, they find their items taken. It disappears in the night after every performance.
name: Bard Purrloin

description: These Pokémon live in solitude. Their fluffy fur absorbs damage, even if they strike foes with a fierce headbutt.
name: Minotaur Bouffalant

description: Apparently, this Pokémon is born when an evil spirit inhabits a sword. It attaches itself to people and drinks their life force.
name: Cursed Blade Honedge

description: Within dense forests, this Pokémon lives in a grove with others of its kind. It’s focused on the health of the forest and sees it as its purpose to keep the forest alive.
name: Druid Zarude

description: It survived many hunts that led it to take on a unique appearance and gain special powers.
name: Barbarian Bloodmoon Ursaluna

description: When it unleashes its psychic power from the protuberance on its head, the sound of music and dance echoes through the area.
name: Pride Queen Bruxish

description: This Crocalor loves camping, and is an expert at starting fires. It wears a hat to protect other camp members from getting burned when they stand close.
name: Proud Crocalor

description: Its three heads think independently. However, they respect each other and never appear to squabble.
name: Celebrating Alolan Exeggutor ft. Komala

description: Its sturdy, curved claws are ideal for traversing precipitous cliffs. From the tips of these claws drips a venom that infiltrates the nerves of any prey caught in Sneasel’s grasp.
name: Hisuian Sneasel

description: Ludicrously strong—when it butts heads with a mountain, it is the mountain that shatters. But its short legs struggle with turns, and it is incapable of stopping unless it collides with something.
name: Rhyhorn

description: Rapidly rotates its horn to bore through bedrock. It swaggers around volcanic regions, protected from the lava’s heat by its tough, armorlike hide.
name: Rhydon

description: It swims at a steady five knots. If it senses danger, it will strike back with its sharp horn.
name: Goldeen

description: To protect its family, it will fight with its drill-sharp horn. It lives in hollowed rocks in streams.
name: Seaking

description: The sharp scythes on its forearms become increasingly sharp by cutting through hard objects.
name: Scyther

description: In the distant past, it was somewhat stronger than the horribly weak descendants that exist today.
name: Magikarp

description: It loves the nectar of flowers and can locate flower patches that have even tiny amounts of pollen.
name: Butterfree

description: It appears whenever there is world conflict, burning down any place it travels through.
name: Gyarados

description: Its genetic code is irregular. It may mutate if it is exposed to radiation from element stones.
name: Eevee

description: Its breath has the fantastic ability to revive dead plants and flowers.
name: Meganium

description: It’s so timid that it can’t move unless it’s with a swarm. It conveys its feelings through scent.
name: Ledyba

description: It uses starlight as energy. When more stars appear at night, the patterns on its back grow larger.
name: Ledian

description: This odd Pokémon can see both the past and the future. It eyes the sun’s movement all day.
name: Xatu

description: To avoid being attacked, it does nothing but mimic a tree. It hates water and flees from rain.
name: Sudowoodo

description: A group of Poliwag and Poliwhirl will form with a Politoed as the leader. Politoed’s cries make the Pokémon of the group obey.
name: Politoed

description: This treetop dweller possesses a tail as dexterous as a hand. Ancient writings describe this Pokémon as a one-armed oddity.
name: Aipom

description: When the temperature cools in the evening, they emerge from water to seek food along the shore.
name: Wooper

description: A dim-witted Pokémon. It doesn’t care if it bumps its head into boats or rocks while swimming.
name: Quagsire

description: If spotted, it will lure an unwary person into chasing it, then lose the pursuer on mountain trails.
name: Murkrow

description: It’s cautious in the extreme, and its hardy vitality lets it live in any kind of environment.
name: Rattata

description: It desperately tries to keep its black tail hidden. This behavior is said to be proof that its tail hides a secret.
name: Wobbuffet

description: Girafarig’s tail has a small head. It instinctively bites at any foe that approaches the Pokémon from behind.
name: Girafarig

description: Its tail is tipped by a thick, horrible stinger. To bring down prey, it will first obscure their vision by covering their faces with its body, and then it will use the stinger to inject them with venom.
name: Gligar

description: This Pokémon evolved through use of a strange item. Its body is coated with steel powder and notably hard—not even diamond can leave so much as a scratch.
name: Steelix

description: It whittles down its constantly growing fangs by gnawing on hard things. It can chew apart cinder block walls.
name: Raticate

description: It swings its eye-patterned pincers up to scare its foes. This makes it look like it has three heads.
name: Scizor

description: With its herculean powers, it can easily throw around an object that is 100 times its own weight.
name: Heracross

description: This is a smart and sneaky Pokémon. A pair may work together to steal eggs by having one lure the parents away.
name: Sneasel

description: It is quite skilled at climbing trees. If it comes across a Primeape while searching for berries in the treetops, trouble will surely ensue.
name: Ursaring

description: The long fur of this Pokémon covers its eyes, ears, and even limbs, allowing Piloswine to resist harshly frigid conditions. The Pokémon’s white tusks can be used to defeat its enemies.
name: Piloswine

description: While Octillery still shoots water from its mouth, the drastic anatomical difference between it and Remoraid meant that for a long time, no one believed the former evolved from the latter.
name: Octillery

description: Upon hearing its eerie howls, other Pokémon get the shivers and head straight back to their nests.
name: Houndoom

description: Donphan is normally a calm Pokémon, but once it is enraged, it will curl its body into a ball and charge at you while rolling.
name: Donphan

description: A fire burns inside it, so it feels very warm to hug. It launches fireballs of 1,800 degrees Fahrenheit.
name: Torchic

description: Its kicking mastery lets it loose 10 kicks per second. It emits sharp cries to intimidate foes.
name: Combusken

description: Flames spout from its wrists, enveloping its knuckles. Its punches scorch its foes.
name: Blaziken

description: When several of these Pokémon gather, their electricity can build and cause lightning storms.
name: Pikachu

description: A colorful and incredibly beautiful but also greedy Pokémon. In an effort to keep its favorite food all to itself, it will chase away Combee as they try to gather nectar.
name: Beautifly

description: Tends to be drawn to bonfires on dark nights. Difficult to chase away from settlements because of the way it scatters highly toxic scales.
name: Dustox

description: If the electric pouches in its cheeks become fully charged, both ears will stand straight up.
name: Raichu

description: If it hears festive music, all its muscles fill with energy. It can’t help breaking out into a dance.
name: Ludicolo

description: The sound of its grass flute makes its listeners uneasy. It lives deep in the forest.
name: Nuzleaf

description: By flapping its leafy fans, it can whip up gusts of 100 feet per second that can level houses.
name: Shiftry

description: It meditates to heighten its inner energy and to float in the air. It eats one berry a day.
name: Meditite

description: It elegantly avoids attacks with dance-like steps, then launches a devastating blow in the same motion.
name: Medicham

description: Though beautiful, it has highly poisonous thorns. There is an old tradition in my homeland wherein one would send these thorns to an opponent to challenge them to a duel.
name: Roselia

description: It has a small heart and brain. Its stomach comprises most of its body, with enzymes to dissolve anything.
name: Gulpin

description: It can swallow a tire whole in one gulp. It secretes a horribly toxic fluid from the pores on its body.
name: Swalot

description: The flaming magma it stores in the hump on its back is the source of its tremendous power.
name: Numel

description: If angered, the humps on its back erupt in a shower of molten lava. It lives in the craters of volcanoes.
name: Camerupt

description: It lives in deserts. It becomes active at night when it hunts for prey exhausted from the desert’s heat.
name: Cacturne

description: It is the world’s most beautiful Pokémon. There are many works of art featuring Milotic.
name: Milotic

description: This rare Pokémon was discovered during a deep-sea exploration. It has not changed in over 100 million years.
name: Relicanth

description: Because they are weak individually, they form groups. However, they bicker if the group grows too big.
name: Starly

description: They maintain huge flocks, although fierce scuffles break out between various flocks.
name: Staravia

description: It never stops attacking even if it is injured. It fusses over the shape of its comb.
name: Staraptor

description: Bidoof has an unsophisticated face and is rarely flustered by anything. There have been incidents involving Bidoof sauntering into villages and gnawing on the houses without a single care.
name: Bidoof

description: After a rainy day, the flower on its back smells stronger. The scent attracts other Pokémon.
name: Venusaur

description: Bibarel fur repels water and is also a fantastic material for heat retention. These Pokémon create dams on rivers to live in.
name: Bibarel

description: When its antennae hit each other, it sounds like the music of a xylophone.
name: Kricketot

description: There is a village that hosts a contest based on the amazingly variable cries of this Pokémon.
name: Kricketune

description: The extension and contraction of its muscles generates electricity. Its fur glows when it’s in trouble.
name: Shinx

description: By gathering their tails together, they collectively generate powerful electricity from their claws.
name: Luxio

description: Luxray’s ability to see through objects comes in handy when it’s scouting for danger.
name: Luxray

description: Hidden within the bouquet on each hand are thorned whips loaded with virulent poison. Roserade moves gracefully as it corners its prey and mercilessly lashes them with its whips.
name: Roserade

description: The trio is together from birth. It constantly gathers nectar from flowers to please Vespiquen.
name: Combee

description: A pair may be seen rubbing their cheek pouches together in an effort to share stored electricity.
name: Pachirisu

description: It inflates its flotation sac, keeping its face above water in order to watch for prey movement.
name: Buizel

description: It is a common sight around fishing ports. It is known to rescue people and help fishers carry what they caught.
name: Floatzel

description: Makes its home in gloomy caves. Atrophied eyes have left this Pokémon blind, so it scans its surroundings via sound waves that it emits from its mouth as it flies.
name: Zubat

description: To affirm their kinship, members of this species will form a ring by linking their newly doubled tails together. On rare occasions, humans have been accepted into such rings.
name: Ambipom

description: It sinks its sharp fangs into other creatures and slurps up their blood. A closer look at the fangs reveals that they are hollow and akin to straws.
name: Golbat

description: It nests in horizontal holes warmed by geothermal heat. Foes who get too close can expect to be pounced on and bitten.
name: Gible

description: It loves sparkly things. It seeks treasures in caves and hoards the loot in its nest.
name: Gabite

description: The protuberances on its head serve as sensors. It can even detect distant prey.
name: Garchomp

description: It shrouds itself in sand to ward off germs. It travels easily through the sands of the desert.
name: Hippopotas

description: The nectar it drools from its mouth smells so atrocious that it can make noses curl from more than a mile away.
name: Gloom

description: It brandishes its gaping mouth in a display of fearsome strength. It raises vast quantities of sand while attacking.
name: Hippowdon

description: It rarely fights fairly, but that is strictly to ensure survival. It is popular as a mascot.
name: Croagunk

description: It has a poison sac at its throat. When it croaks, the stored poison is churned for greater potency.
name: Toxicroak

description: It absorbs sunlight with the pink areas of its skin, which then shine. This appears to be a form of camouflage.
name: Finneon

description: Lumineon swimming in the darkness of the deep sea look like stars shining in the night sky.
name: Lumineon

description: Seemingly curious about people, they gather around footsteps they find on snowy mountains.
name: Snover

description: Its petals are the largest in the world. As it walks, it scatters extremely allergenic pollen.
name: Vileplume

description: They appear when the snow flowers bloom. When the petals fall, they retreat to places unknown again.
name: Abomasnow

description: They travel in groups of four or five, leaving signs for one another on trees and rocks. They bring down their prey with coordinated attacks.
name: Weavile

description: This Pokémon evolved through use of a curious item. Its rocklike hide is composed of a mysterious substance and can withstand a blow from a masterwork sword with nary a scratch.
name: Rhyperior

description: Draped with long vines, it resembles a shrub in appearance. It swings bundles of vines as though they were arms, wrapping them around prey to ensnare them.
name: Tangrowth

description: This species reached its zenith during the period known as the ice age. I suspect that Hisui’s frigid climate is in harmony with Mamoswine’s constitution, thus awakening hidden potential.
name: Mamoswine

description: It has a small heart and brain. Its stomach comprises most of its body along with beansprouts and other fillings, all wrapped in nori.
name: Temaki Gulpin

description: Its vibrant, colorful fur shines brightly as it flies through the sky, guiding spirits to their loved ones on Día de Muertos.
name: Alebrije Pyroar

description: The aroma that rises from the flowers contains a substance that makes anyone happy.
name: Shamrock Meganium

description: It lives in groups by the water. During Easter, it plays the role of Easter Bunny for nearby villages to entertain the children.
name: Easter Bidoof

description: By allowing its cry to resonate in the hollow of its belly, it produces magic.
name: Wizard Kricketune

description: It is a common sight around cave entrances. It is known to rescue people and keep evil at bay.
name: Ranger Floatzel

description: Its knuckle claws secrete a toxin that is used for battles in dungeons.
name: Rogue Toxicroak

description: Males have plumage on their heads. They will never let themselves feel close to anyone other than their Trainers.
name: Unfezant

description: Using the invisible poison spikes on its veillike arms and legs, it paralyzes its enemies and causes them to drown.
name: Frillish

description: Fishermen are terrified of Jellicent. It’s rumored to drag them into the sea and steal their lives away.
name: Jellicent

description: There are rumors that a child with mystical powers became a Kadabra; however, this remains unverified. I suspect that the spoon Kadabra holds enhances its brain waves.
name: Kadabra

description: The longer Alakazam lives, the larger and heavier its head becomes. Our tests have shown that the strength of its psychic powers correlates positively to the weight of its head.
name: Alakazam

description: The mane of a male Pyroar heats up to over 3,600 degrees Fahrenheit during battle. Merely approaching it will cause severe burns.
name: Pyroar

description: The eyeball patterns on the interior of its ears emit psychic energy. It keeps the patterns tightly covered because that power is too immense.
name: Meowstic

description: The brains in its two heads appear to communicate emotions to each other with a telepathic power.
name: Doduo

description: When Doduo evolves into this odd breed, one of its heads splits into two. This Pokémon runs at nearly 40 mph.
name: Dodrio

description: This Pokémon never leaves its Trainer’s side. It predicts their actions with its psychic power and takes care of their day-to-day needs.
name: Indeedee

description: Clads itself in the souls of comrades that perished before fulfilling their goals of journeying upstream. No other species throughout all Hisui’s rivers is Basculegion’s equal.
name: Basculegion

description: It entrances female Pokémon with the sweet, alluring scent that wafts from all over its body.
name: Oinkologne

description: Always holding a pendulum that it swings at a steady rhythm, it causes drowsiness in anyone nearby.
name: Hypno
